title: hot dogs in a bun
directions: Thaw dough.
Cut small slices of dough and flatten; wrap dough around hot dogs and bake until brown.
The kids love them.

title: grasshopper torte
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; reserve 1/2 cup.
Press remaining crumbs onto bottom of a 9-inch pie dish.
Chill. Combine marshmallow cream and creme de menthe.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Freeze.

title: one bowl buttercream frosting
directions: Beat butter and sugar together. Add cocoa alternately with milk, beating to spreading consistency. Stir in vanilla. Makes about 2 cups.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Cook frozen vegetables until just tender. Drain kidney beans, then mix all vegetables together.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; blend well.
Blend for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool 15 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, or spread whipped topping.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine water, bouillon cubes, onion and garlic and let stand 10 minutes.
Add to mixture, oil, vinegar, tarragon and pepper. Place potatoes in shallow 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour dressing over all, tossing to coat.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, until potatoes are fork-tender, about 35 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve at room temperature on lettuce leaves or as a hot vegetable dish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: plain doughnuts
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream until light. Stir in beaten eggs.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Stir in vanilla. Chill thoroughly.
Roll out 1/3-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut with flour cutter.
Fry in hot deep fat (375°) until brown.
Turn over once.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Brown meat 5 minutes on all sides.
Spread salt and pepper on meat.
Spread horseradish over meat.
Place potatoes, carrots and onions around meat.
Cover.
Cook in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together well by hand and chill.
Yields 2 cups.

title: carrots supreme
directions: Cut carrots and cook until tender.
Cut bacon in 1-inch pieces and fry until crisp; drain.
Dice cheese.
Mix all ingredients and put into greased casserole.
Top with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° in covered dish for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Beat butter in bowl, when softened, beat in sugar, flour and semolina. Mix until it is dough. Roll out lightly. Put on cooking pan. Prick shortbread all over using a fork.
Bake for 1 1\4 hour on center shelf in oven. While warm mark the surface, using a knife into wedges. Let cool.
Store in air-tight tin.

title: crab boats
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Chop crab meat.
Rinse mushrooms in cold water; dry and remove stems.
Combine soup, crumbs, mayo, spices (seasonings) and crab.
Stuff each mushroom with a tablespoon of crab mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Place on well buttered baking pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in	small
saucepan.
Add oysters, cook and stir over low heat just until edges curl.
Heat milk and cream in another saucepan.
Stir
in
salt and pepper.
Makes four 1 cup servings.

title: elephant stew
directions: Use largest pot you can find.
Simmer about 7 weeks.
Spice to taste.
Remove rabbit (no one likes hare in his stew).
Serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits.
Blend condensed milk, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Pour over fruit and nuts.
Put in refrigerator.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Microwave (or boil) 6 tea bags in 2 quarts of water (about 10 to 15 minutes in microwave).
Pour into 1 gallon pitcher.
Add sugar and cranberry juice, then add enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, water and butter in saucepan. Bring to boil and cool, stirring occasionally, to soft ball stage (236° on candy thermometer).
This takes about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly.
Add cream, salt and vanilla. Beat well.
Serve warm or cold over ice cream.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and vanilla plus vegetable oil.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix well to first mixture.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased sheets.
Press down with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake until golden brown.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 375°.

title: prune-nut bread(yields 1 loaf)
directions: Combine prune juice and water in a small saucepan; bring to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in prunes and butter.
Cool mixture to lukewarm.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour and remaining ingredients in large bowl; add prune mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: appetizer cheesecake
directions: Combine the tortilla chips and butter and press in the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, place the cottage cheese in a blender or food processor.
Cover and process on high speed until smooth.
In a large bowl of an electric mixer, combine the cottage cheese and cream cheese, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Add the eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in Cheddar cheese and chiles.
Pour the mixture over the baked crust.
Return the pan to the oven and bake for 1 hour.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray Pam in glass baking dish.
Place turkey legs/thighs in dish.
Spray Pam on turkey legs/thighs directly. Sprinkle garlic powder, tarragon, salt and pepper on turkey.
Place turkey on bottom rack in preheated oven.
Cook 40 minutes. Lower oven to 350°.
Turn turkey over.
Spray with Pam. Sprinkle with seasonings.
Cook 1 hour.

Baste turkey with juices. Cook an additional 20 to 30 minutes until turkey is done. Reserve juices and add 1 teaspoon cornstarch previously dissolved in 2 teaspoons warm water. Slice turkey and allow gravy to settle in legs.
Wait about 5 to 10 minutes, then serve.

title: easy triangle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough about 1/4-inch thick.
Lay in a 13 x 9-inch pan overlapping if necessary.
Bake 15 minutes until golden and puffy.
Remove pan from oven and sprinkle chocolate and peanut butter chips over hot cookie layer. Let stand a few minutes until melted.
Swirl topping with back of metal spoon.
Cool.
Cut into triangles.

title: three-cheese baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta according to package directions; rinse and drain.
In a large saucepan, melt butter, add onion, and saute until tender.
Add instant bouillon; stir until dissolved.
Stir in flour to make a roux.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes until browned, stirring constantly.
Slowly whisk in milk, until mixture is smooth.
Add all three cheeses; stir over low heat until completely melted.
Put cooked pasta into a 2-quart casserole dish and pour sauce over, gently tossing to coat evenly. Sprinkle with bread crumbs (and additional Parmesan cheese if desired).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, or until browned and bubbly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Beat until creamy. Add vanilla.
Combine salt, soda, baking powder and flour or use 2 1/2 cups self-rising flour and leave out other 3 ingredients.
Add a small amount at a time to sugar mixture.
Add apples and pecans. Mix by hand.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan which has been greased. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Process bananas and margarine 20 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients and process 10 seconds.
Do not overprocess; this will make bread coarse.

title: grandma brown's polish raisin cake
directions: Simmer first 7 ingredients for 5 minutes and cool.
Dissolve baking soda in 1 teaspoon water.
Add mixture to flour.
Stir by hand 10 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured/nonstick tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Check if done with toothpick.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Sprinkle on coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in layers.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over top.
Sprinkle on nuts and press lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Remove from bone and cut into bit size pieces. Save broth. Dice celery and onion, add to broth and cook until tender. Add spaghetti to broth and cook until tender. Drain, but save broth.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Top with 2 tablespoons of margarine and cover with cheese slices.
Put 1/4 cup crumbled crackers on top. Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Last 5 minutes, uncover to brown.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Remove from bone and cut into pieces.
Reserve stock.
Into a large kettle, place vegetables (except peas) into stock and cook until tender.
Add peas and cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until just below boiling.
Yields 3 quarts.
For lighter soup, use low-sodium soup, low-fat milk and low-fat cheese.
Chicken and stock may be prepared ahead and frozen.
Serve with salad and toasted bread.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, salt and boiling water together.
Set aside and cool. Add beaten eggs and warm water to shortening mixture.
Mix yeast with 3 cups flour and sift into shortening mixture. Add the 3 remaining cups of flour, blending well. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: spinach souffle stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In saucepan, using 3 tablespoons butter or oil, saute the onion, garlic, celery and carrot until softened. Add the parsley, mustard, cooked bacon, cooked sausage and the lemon-pepper seasoning.
Remove the stems from the mushrooms and chop finely.
Then saute them in 1 tablespoon butter until softened and any water they release is cooked away.
Mix them with the rest of the stuffing mixture.

title: twice baked potato
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prick potatoes a few times with a fork. Bake for 1 hour or until soft.
Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out the pulp.
Put in a bowl. Separate eggs.
Add egg yolks to potato pulp.
Stir and blend until smooth.
Add butter and cream.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into potato mixture.
Fill potato shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for about 15 minutes or until heated through. Sauteed onion, chopped parsley, sauteed peppers or sauteed mushrooms may be added.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together and top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spring onion rings
directions: Slice onions 1-inch thick.

Separate onion slices into rings. Place rings in large bowl of ice water and let soak for 5 minutes. In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour, baking powder, buttermilk, egg, oil, paprika and pepper to form batter.
In deep-fat fryer, heat oil to 350°.
Place remaining 1 1/2 cups flour in small bowl.

title: green chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Season with lots of salt. Sprinkle the flour over the burger.
Add tomatoes which have been crushed down to pulp.
Add diced green chilies and can of water. Bring to boil.
Turn off heat and let set for 10 minutes, then serve with cheese flavored Doritos.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in small pieces.
Wash.
Fry bacon and crumble up.
Mix bacon and broccoli in bowl.
Add cheese, onion and raisins. Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture and stir.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: bean or pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cover with water.
Cook on low overnight.

title: syrian eggplant
directions: Peel and boil eggplant for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and mash with a fork.
Brown meat, pepper, onion and seasonings in 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in eggplant and rice.
Pour into a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan.
Top with crumbs and remaining butter.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: choco-crunch brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Spread marshmallow cream over top. Melt the chocolate chips and peanut butter; stir in Rice Krispies. Spread over the marshmallow layer.
Chill before cutting.
Store in refrigerator.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add whipping cream.
Continue to beat.
Add Eagle Brand milk, then peaches.
Pour into can.
Add milk and swirl with paddle.
Freeze in ice cream freezer according to freezer instructions.

title: aunt janet's chicken broccoli chowder
directions: Add onion and celery to broth, simmer while preparing potatoes. Season with salt and simmer until tender.
Cook broccoli separately until slightly undercooked.
Add broccoli to vegetables along with 2 cups diced chicken.
Set aside while preparing Cream Sauce.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in beef, onion flakes, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and bell pepper.
Mix well. Stir in sour cream. Spoon mixture into an 8-inch pie plate or small shallow baking dish. Sprinkle nuts over top. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Serve hot with assorted crackers.

title: salmon party log
directions: Combine salmon with other ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into log or ball.
Cover with chopped pecans and serve with crackers. Chill well.
Best when made several hours before serving.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix together and chill. Great spread for crackers.

title: cold cranberry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
To make pretty or festive for parties, save some Cool Whip for top and use a few whole cranberries for topping.
Keep refrigerated until ready to eat.

title: garlic cheese chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
Arrange in pan.
Melt oleo.
Sprinkel chicken with garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with melted oleo and refrigerate 1 hour.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 1 hour, basting after 1/2 hour.

title: best sweet potatoes
directions: You will need a 3-quart dish.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together instant pudding mix, milk, condensed milk and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
In large bowl, place 1 layer each of wafers and banana slices.
Spoon pudding mixture over layers until covered. Continue layering evenly.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Decorate with additional wafers, if desired.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice evenly in lightly greased casserole.
Spoon vegetables over rice.
Pour chicken broth and water over all. Cook sausage until brown; drain well.
Spoon sausage over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir well.
Cover and bake for an additional 30 minutes. Garnish with mushrooms and parsley, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: white sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and cook until thick.

title: deer chili
directions: Brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Drain all fat and add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for about one hour.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saut garlic and onion. Broil tomatoes on all sides until skin begins to char. Peel and pure in blender with garlic and onion, adding 1/4 cup stock if needed. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large pan over high heat. Add pure; cook and stir 2 minutes. Lower heat; cook and stir 5 to 10 minutes more, until pure thickens a bit and changes color. Add remaining chicken stock, epazote, cilantro, cubed chicken, salt and pepper to taste and cook 15 minutes or so. Add tortilla chips. May garnish with Feta cheese (this is yummy) or Cheddar, lime juice (this adds some zip) and chopped avocados.
Serves 6. Can freeze, without tortilla chips and avocado. Can do ahead.

title: diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, and pudding mix until smooth.
Turn into pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice with smoked ham
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of the butter in a saucepan.
Add the onion. Cook, stirring, until the onion is wilted.
Add the ham and rice and stir to blend.
Add the broth, salt and bay leaf and cover. Bring to a boil and then simmer for 17 minutes.
Stir in the remaining 1 tablespoon of butter.
Remove the bay leaf and serve. Yields 4 servings.

title: coconut dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spoon pineapple over top of pie filling.
Spread dry cake mix over pineapple; even out with fork.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut over cake.
Sprinkle pecans over coconut. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(Use regular cake mix, not one that calls for oil.)

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars and 1 stick oleo.
Set aside to cool. Cream sugar and 1 stick oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add flour, soda and buttermilk alternately.
Add melted candy and oleo mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325° or until done.
(I put pecans in frosting instead of cake.)
Frost cake with Milky Way Cake Frosting.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix zucchini and onion, stir in flour until vegetables are well coated.
Add other ingredients.
Spray square baking dish with cooking spray, pour in mixture and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together 1 cup butter, 2 cups flour and the powdered sugar.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine lemon juice, eggs, sugar and salt; mix well. Add baking powder and flour; mix well.
Spread on hot, baked layer; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When done, sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Cool; slice into bars.

title: tzimmes
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in ungreased mold or casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated avocados and tomatoes
directions: Dressing: Prepare dressing by blending the first nine ingredients listed above. Set aside.

title: shrimp smorbrod
directions: In a medium bowl, mix shrimp, peas, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt to blend.
Cut 3 slices of firm sourdough rye bread in half.
Spread each slice of bread with butter and top with lettuce leaf.
Mound about 1/4 cup shrimp mixture on top of lettuce. Cover and refrigerate several hours.
To serve, cut lemon slices very thin from edge to center.
Twist and place on shrimp mixture.

title: beef and lima bean dinner
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet, stirring often to crumble beef; drain.
Stir in lima beans and barbecue sauce; heat until bubbly.
Spoon meat mixture into a lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with cheese.
Separate each biscuit into 2 halves, making 10 biscuit rounds.
Place rounds on top of casserole, overlapping edges if necessary.
Bake, uncovered at 375° for 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Stir constantly into water and heat until boiling.
Stir in bouillon cubes until dissolved.
Add chopped mushrooms to mixture and simmer 20 minutes.
Add milk and seasonings.
Yields 4 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine onion, 2 tablespoons oil, poppy seed, sugar, salt and dry mustard in a bowl; beat thoroughly.
Gradually add oil, then vinegar.
Pour into jar with tight-fitting lid and refrigerate. Shake the jar vigorously before serving.
Yields almost 2 cups. (May be prepared ahead of time.)

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a small bowl.
Beat until well blended and thickened.
Place in a covered container and chill several hours.
Shake before serving.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: fried piesroswell, new mexico
directions: * Whatever kind of pies you happen to want.
Has to be ready to use filling - apple, peach, cherry, applesauce - let your conscience be your guide.

title: onions au gratin
directions: Peel and slice onions, arrange in baking dish, overlapping slices.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Add thyme and pour over onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with margarine.
Cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Toss bread crumbs with the melted margarine.
Add cheese. Sprinkle crumbs and cheese over onions.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes longer.

title: meat loaf roll-up
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, tomato sauce, Worcestershire, oregano, pepper, salt and oatmeal in a large bowl.
On waxed paper, pat meat mixture into rectangle approximately 8 x 10-inches.
Arrange ham slices on top of meat, leaving a small margin around the edges.
Sprinkle cheese on top of ham.
Starting from a short end, carefully roll up meat; seal edges and ends. Place roll, seam side down, in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon drops
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat thoroughly.
Add boiling water.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture gradually, mixing well after each addition.

title: summer dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables.
Yields 2 1/4 cups.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan; let thaw.
Mix together 1/2 cup melted oleo, the cream of chicken soup, cheese, sour cream and onions.
Mix and spread over thawed potatoes.
Top with the crushed corn flakes; drizzle 3/4 stick of oleo over all. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes, onions, celery and eggs.

title: cheesy chicken breast surprise
directions: Spray bottom of glass baking dish with Pam. Place chicken in dish and place a slice of cheese on each breast. Mix soup and water and spread over all. Melt oleo and mix with stuffing mix; spread over all. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and peanut butter. Add 1 cup granulated sugar and the brown sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture until well combined.
Using level tablespoon for each, shape into 5 dozen balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove and press an unwrapped chocolate kiss on top of each.
Bake 2 minutes longer.
Remove cookies to wire rack; let cool completely.

title: egg nog
directions: Blend
yolks
until
light;
add
sugar
and beat until thick. Stir in milk, flavoring and whipped topping.
Top with nutmeg after chilling for 1 hour if desired.

title: no-fat matzoh balls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Gradually stir in matzoh meal; keep stirring until mixture is pretty thick.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Make balls about the size of large walnuts.
Drop into boiling, salted water.
Let boil for about 25 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 rather large balls.

title: herb-baked chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in oil, salt, pepper, garlic and herbs for 12 to 24 hours.
Remove chicken; shake in bag with flour and paprika. Put in large baking dish; pour rest of marinade over it.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes on each side at 350°.

title: lentil stew
directions: Boil water; add lentils.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add potato and carrot and cook 30 minutes more.
Add sauce and broth; cook 15 minutes more.
Serve with corn muffins or salad.
(Serves 4.)

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Pour cake icing out onto a piece of wax paper.
Knead small amounts of powdered sugar into the cake icing.
You want the mixture to be dry enough to roll out good.
Use a rolling pin to roll into a thin rectangular shape. Spread peanut butter all over the dough.
Roll up into a long roll.
Cut into small pieces. Stack into a container, placing wax paper between layers. Refrigerate.

title: white potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Add sugar, butter, salt and beaten egg yolks to hot potatoes.
Add milk and flavorings.
Fold in egg whites, which have been stiffly beaten.
The mixture should be fairly thin.
Bake in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake an additional 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions in salted water until tender; drain.
Arrange stalks in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken atop.
Combine next 3 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter, sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until heated through.
Trim with pimiento strips if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add water and bananas.
Thoroughly mix in flour, soda and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured bread or cake pan.
Bake in covered crock-pot on high for 2 to 3 hours, or until done.

title: granny's simple stew
directions: Place the first 6 ingredients in crock-pot.
Combine the soup and water.
Pour over ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot all day. Usually start pot on high, then reduce to low all day.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme.
Add juice and rind.
Good dip for apples, pineapple, bananas, etc.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 5 cups.

title: venezuelan mystery pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Heat cornmeal, broth and garlic salt to boiling in 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and egg; fold in Colby cheese.
Spread cornmeal mixture on bottom and sides of pie plate.
Flute edges using oiled fingers.
Cook ground beef in 10-inch skillet, stirring frequently, until brown; drain.
Stir in bell pepper, onion and olives.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in salsa; simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Spoon beef mixture into pie plate. Cover with aluminum foil; bake 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Mix sour cream, Cheddar cheese and mayo.
Spread over beef mixture. Bake uncovered 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving. Garnish with paprika, bell pepper slices and green onion curls if desired.

title: golden punch
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Add lemonade, water, pineapple juice and almond and vanilla extracts.
Allow punch to stand for several hours in refrigerator to allow flavors to blend.
Remove from refrigerator about 1 hour before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Mold with hands.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate for 12 hours or more.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones.
Add margarine to broth.
Put chicken back into broth and bring to boil.

title: viennese coffee(6 servings)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl and beat until stiff. Place a cinnamon stick in each cup and fill with coffee.
Spoon whipped cream on top and garnish with orange peels.
Serve at once.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place first 7 ingredients,
in a 9 x 12-inch pan, in layers, in order as given.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise; spread over salad.
Garnish with Cheddar cheese.
Chill for 8 hours.

title: glazed sweet potatoes(something like franke's cafeteria's candied sweets.)
directions: Peel potatoes and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Combine margarine, 1/2 cup of the sugar and water in a 12-inch frying pan.
Boil for 1 to 2 minutes, until sugar is dissolved.
Add potato slices to pan; stir to coat well.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes, until tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Do not overcook.
Add remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Reduce heat to low; cook, uncovered, another 4 to 5 minutes.
Again, do not overcook.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets (use juice as directed).
Dissolve jello in hot beet and orange juice.
Add salt, horseradish and vinegar.
Cool to soft jell stage, then add celery, onion and beets.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Unmold on salad greens or scoop out with ice cream scoop onto salad greens.
Yields 5 cups.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: "fut-shi"
directions: Wash all of vegetables.
Cut to small pieces.
Mix vegetables together.
Blend garlic, salt, lemon juice and vinegar together; brown pita bread and add to salad.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, eggs and water.
Beat for 4 minutes, then add the salad oil and mix well.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°. While cake is still warm, punch full of holes. Mix powdered sugar, lemon juice and rind and pour over hot cake.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, soda, salt, and sugar; stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased 10 inch iron skillet. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: french creme icing
directions: Add milk gradually to flour and stir until smooth.
Cook in double boiler.
Stir constantly until thick.
Cook mixture.
Keep covered and stir occasionally to avoid lumps.
When creamed, add cooled flour and milk mixture on slow speed.
When blended, beat for 15 minutes at medium speed.
Add flavoring as desired.
Use on Red Velvet cake or any cake.

title: carrot drumsticks
directions: Cook carrots and mash.
Add chopped pepper, minced onion, soft breadcrumbs, egg, chopped celery and salt and pepper.
Mix together and form into oval shaped patties.
Roll in dry breadcrumbs.
Fry in large frying pan with small amount of vegetable oil.
This was a World War II meat substitute dish my mother made.
We ate them with catsup.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together and beat in 3 cups of chopped apple and 1 1/2 cups pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: "dirt"
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in crushed Oreos.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Reserve some Oreos for top.)
Beat 8 ounces cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix vanilla pudding as to directions, leaving out 1 cup milk.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with reserved cookies (crushed) and chill.

title: marinated mushrooms and hazelnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread hazelnuts on baking sheet; toast in oven until aromatic, about 10 minutes.
Rub nuts with a kitchen towel to remove their papery skins.
Coarsely chop nuts and set aside.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn. Chop onions and tomato and add to the corn. Mix and add the rest of the ingredients. Serve cold.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until almost done.
Rinse.
Brown hamburger. Season with salt and pepper.
Spray lasagna pan with cooking spray.
Layer noodles, hamburger, sauce and cheese.
Repeat as many times as necessary.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak in half and season with salt and pepper.
Place onion slices in crock-pot.
Place meat on top of onion.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease cookie sheet. Beat shortening and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.

Combine oats, flour, baking soda. Add to creamed mixture; mix well. Add water, mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoons onto prepared cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Should make about 2 1/2 doz. cookies.

title: stuffed mirlitons(vegetable pears)
directions: Boil mirlitons.
Allow to cool.
Scrape out pulp by cutting in half.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add shrimp and crabmeat.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Place mixture in shells.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: snuffles truffles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Roll into balls, then roll in crumbs and chill.

title: dynasty duckling pizza imperiale(makes about 16 servings)
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Combine rice, pecans, egg, 1/2 cup of the Swiss cheese and 1/4 cup of the Parmesan cheese in a large bowl. Grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
Evenly press rice mixture onto bottom and up side of pan to create a 1/2-inch rim. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch; line bottom with wax paper and grease paper.
Sift dry ingredients onto another wax paper. Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until again fluffy.
Stir alternately flour with mashed bananas; fold in pecans and orange rind.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until golden or pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Peel off paper.
Let cool completely.
Wrap and store overnight for easier slicing.

title: jesse's favorite potato soup
directions: Combine potato slices and onion; cover with water.
Cook on medium heat until potatoes are soft.
Mash the potatoes in the water that they are cooked in.
Add margarine and milk.
Simmer 10 minutes or until hot.

title: large crazy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together first 5 ingredients and put in mixing bowl.
Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and water.
Mix together, but not with mixer.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes.

title: shotgun sauce
directions: Mix sauce and let stand at room temperature.
Pour over hot vegetable.
Serve over peas, limas or green beans.

title: cranberry nut loaf
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine orange juice, grated rind with egg.
Pour all at once into dry ingredients, mixing only enough to dampen dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Put in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, lightly greased.
Spread corners and sides slightly higher than center.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Cuts better if a day old.

title: christmas morning breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and spread with butter. Place them side by side in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Brown sausage and crumble; drain. Layer over bread slices. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine eggs, half and half and salt and mix well. Cover and chill Christmas Eve night. Bake, uncovered, Christmas morning at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Make into a dough and put through a cookie press to form straws or cut into strips.
Cook about 350° until done, usually about 10 to 15 minutes.
(Half a recipe makes 8 dozen.)

title: barbecued weenies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour or may put in crock-pot and serve.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In soup pot, cook chicken in water until done. Remove chicken and shred with a fork. Set aside. Mix flour, shortening and milk. Roll out thin and cut into strips. Drop 1 at a time into boiling broth. After last strip is dropped, allow to cook for 7 minutes. Remove pot from heat. Add evaporated milk and chicken. Stir gently. Cover and let stand for 1 hour. Warm gently before serving.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces in shallow baking dish.
Mix dressing, soup mix and preserves with small amount of water.
Pour over chicken and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is tender. Good with wild rice and green vegetable.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter teddy bear cookies
directions: Mix well all the ingredients together.
Chill the dough for 1/2 hour.

title: lamb blocks with summer squash
directions: Brown lamb blocks well on both sides in heated oil in a large, deep frying pan or Dutch oven.
Add onion, garlic, salt, oregano, pepper and broth.
Bring to boiling.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer until lamb is very tender, 10 to 12 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer lamb and vegetables to a warm serving dish.
Keep warm.

title: colonial carrot pecan cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
In large size mixing bowl combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Add half of flour mixture; blend.
Add remaining flour, alternately with eggs, one at a time; mix well after each addition.
Add carrots and pecans, mix well.
Pour into lightly oiled 10 inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan upright.
Remove from pan.
Frost with Orange Glaze.

title: country chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in a Dutch oven, add water, celery, salt. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat, simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken from broth, and cool.
Discard celery. Bone chicken, cut meat into bite size pieces; set aside meat and 3/4 cup chicken broth.
Leave remaining broth in Dutch oven. Combine flour, baking powder, 1/2 tsp. salt; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
add 3/4 cup reserved broth, stirring with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a well flowered surface, and knead.
Pat dough to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut dough in 4 x 1/2 inch pieces, and sprinkle with additional flour.
Bring broth to a boil.
Drop dough, one piece at a time into boiling broth.
Gently stirring after each addition.
Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in chicken and serve immediately.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: fiery cajun shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a bowl, mix all ingredients, except lemon slices and shrimp.
Pour about 1/2 cup sauce to cover the bottom of a large baking dish and arrange layers of shrimp and lemon slices until nearly to the top of the dish.
Leave about 1-inch headroom.
Pour remaining sauce over shrimp and lemon slices.

title: springerle cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for 15 minutes with mixer at maximum speed. Sift flour and baking powder together; add 2 cups into mixer at a slower speed.
Add lemon rind, then gradually add the balance of flour so dough is quite thick.
Let stand at least 1 hour in refrigerator.
Roll small quantities 1/8-inch thick.
Use flour and turn to keep dough from sticking.
Dust a cookie mold with flour; place dough over mold and press gently.
Turn mold over.
Trim and cut cookies apart and let dry overnight on cloth-covered table with tea towel covering.
Bake next day on lightly greased cookie sheets and sprinkle anise seed on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 325° oven.
Cookies should be turning light brown.
Store in a tin 4 to 6 weeks to soften.

title: oatmeal cookies with filling
directions: Cream first three ingredients together until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, flour, salt, soda and vanilla to the creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal.
Make into balls the size of walnuts. Pat down with floured glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine, mix well and refrigerate.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Roll apples slices up in a dinner roll and place in a large baking dish.
Melt butter, sugar, and cinnamon together and pour over the rolls.
Pour the Mountain Dew over everything.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: yum yum
directions: Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Using half of the mixture, mold into Pyrex dish.

title: pizzelle
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add cooled, melted margarine or oil, vanilla and anise seed.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Dough will be sticky enough to be dropped from spoon.
Bake on hot pizzelle iron until golden and crispy.
Makes about 60 pizzelle cookies.

title: parmesan bruschetta
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small bowl. Stir well. Spread cheese mixture evenly over bread slices. Place bread slices on a baking sheet. Broil until toasted. Makes 4 servings.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix well all dry ingredients.
Beat eggs with buttermilk and oil.
Mix only until all is moistened.
Do not mix again.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chiladas
directions: Place alternate layers of corn chips, chili, onion and cheese in a 1-quart casserole.
End with cheese on top.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until hot.

title: crunchy apple pie
directions: Fill shell with filling and set aside.
Combine flour and brown sugar, cut in margarine until crumbly, mix in walnuts and sprinkle mixture over apple pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
If necessary, cover pie with foil to prevent overbrowning.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Bake pie shells according to package directions and cool. Prepare instant pudding (both packs) as directed and add half of coconut.
Set aside remaining half of coconut.
Fill pie shells with pudding mixture and chill until set.
Top with whipped topping using half a bowl on each.
Sprinkle remaining coconut on pies.

title: holiday punch bowl
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale and mint.
Pour over block of ice in large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Garnish.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Place juice in double boiler. When hot, add sugar, cornstarch, salt and eggs which have been beaten together.
Cook until thick.
Remove from fire and cool. Whip the cream and fold into pudding mixture.
Combine pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour mixture over fruit and stir together.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Can stand overnight.
You can add 1 cup nuts, if desired.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Layer half the potatoes, salt and pepper, onion and ham and dot with margarine.
Repeat layers. Slowly pour in milk just to the top of the potatoes.
Mix 1 cup milk with 2 tablespoons of cornstarch and pour into casserole. Cover with foil and bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: quesadillas
directions: Lightly grease large sheet pan.
Place 1 tortilla in pan. Moisten edge with water.
Place choice of ingredients on tortilla. Moisten edge of another tortilla and place on top of first one, press edges together.
Press down gently to distribute filling. Bake at 400° until lightly browned and thoroughly heated (7 to 10 minutes).
Cut into quarters.
Serve hot with salsa, sour cream, guacamole, etc.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes and cook.
Let drain.
Put mayonnaise, mustard, pickles and as many onions as you like.
Stir in cubed eggs and mix well.
This makes more than you need for 2 or 3 salads.
You can cut down the ingredients.

title: mexican fiestaserves 16great for a spontaneous get-together of any size group
directions: Brown meat and pour off fat, then mix with flour.
Add next 6 ingredients and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except stuffing.
Put on baking dish.
Put stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or bubbly.

title: boston corn bread
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 425° or until done.
Do not overbake.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Drain. Combine vegetables, 1/3 stick margarine, cheese and 10 crushed Ritz crackers until cheese and margarine are melted and well mixed.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle remaining crushed Ritz crackers over top.
Pour 2/3 stick of melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together. Add eggs and beat until mixed. Add milk, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into plate, lightly greased and coated with cornmeal or pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian carbonara
directions: Remove casings from sausage; crumble sausage.
Place a wok over medium heat.
When wok is hot, add sausage and half the Prosciutto (ham); stir-fry about 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Blend remaining Prosciutto with cooked sausage mixture; remove wok from heat.
Add hot tagliarini, butter and parsley to meats.
Mix quickly to blend.
At once pour in eggs and continue to blend, quickly lifting and mixing the pasta to coat well with egg.
Sprinkle in cheese and dash of pepper; mix again.
Serve with additional cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: florida pecan christmas cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and rind. Add vanilla. Add in raisins and pecans.
Add flour, one cup at a time, sifted with salt and baking powder.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 50 minutes.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Cook sugar and sour cream in a heavy pan over medium heat to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat, add vanilla.
Pour over pecan goodies, stirring gently until all are coated.
Use a very large bowl for mixing.
Pour goodies out on a buttered surface
until dry.
Store on shelf in covered container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush crackers.
Add butter and mix well.
Spread 1/2 of the mixture into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with chopped chicken.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Add remaining cracker mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mushroom tarts
directions: Melt butter in pan; cook onion and mushrooms until all moisture has evaporated.
Remove pan from heat; sprinkle flour over mushrooms and stir well.
Add canned milk; bring mixture to a boil.
Simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Fill tiny shells made from your favorite pie crust recipe.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, lemon juice and parsley.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
These freeze well, but will need to bake longer.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Pull the center from the bread.
Pour the chilled dip into the bread.
Use the excess bread to dip.

title: alaska golden halibut
directions: Dip fillets in crumbs and place in a greased baking dish. Combine in a bowl mayo and lemon juice.
Add yogurt or sour cream; blend well.
Fold in egg white.
Sprinkle fillets with onion and spoon mayo mixture on top of fillets.
Sprinkle with almonds and paprika and cheese.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes or until halibut flakes.

title: cream pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes or until pale yellow. Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla, mixing until sugar is dissolved. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to batter alternately with cream. Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until done. Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool. Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix tuna and mayonnaise.
Add relish.
Chop celery and add. Serve on a bed of lettuce with mandarin oranges.
Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable supreme
directions: Combine and cook first 4 ingredients.
Place in casserole dish which has been sprayed with Pam or buttered. Heat soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and another teaspoon minced onion and pour over vegetable mixture.
Top casserole with crumbs which have been mixed with 1/2 stick butter or oleo.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend biscuit mix, grated cheese, shortening, salt and cayenne pepper.
Mix with fork to consistency of coarse crumbs.
Add egg yolk and water to form stiff dough. Knead a few times and roll to 1/4-inch thickness on surface sprinkled with flour.
Cut into strips.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 19 (6 x 1/2-inch) straws.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch; let come to boil.
Add 1 package of strawberry jello; let boil one minute.
Put strawberries in 2 baked pie shells; pour mixture over berries. Cool in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
For a double recipe use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package, drain.
Heat margarine and whipping cream over low until margarine is melted.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over hot noodles, stirring until noodles are well coated.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: sauteed squid
directions: Clean
squid,
taking the inside out.
Cut off the 'eye portion,'
discarding
it,	but
you can cook the legs.
Saute squids
in	frying pan until most of the liquid fills the pan. Drain liquid and saute again until the liquid stops coming out of the
squid.
Stir
in
butter
and	soy sauce.
Simmer few minutes and serve.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Beat butter, sugars, water and egg until light and fluffy.
Stir in nuts, coconut and chips.
Drop by teaspoon or tablespoon (according to size wanted) onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 3 large dozen or 4 small dozen.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Cook potatoes in a little boiling salted water for about 10 minutes or until just tender.
Drain and turn into 1-quart greased casserole.
Add onion, parsley, pimento and green onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Sprinkle with butter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: sour cream, cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Chill for several hours.
This lets flavors blend together.

title: jamaican chicken
directions: Place the chicken between 2 sheets heavy plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4 inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Combine the flour, coconut, 1/2 teaspoon curry powder, salt and pepper. Stir well. Brush both sides of each chicken piece with egg white; dredge in the flour mixture and set aside.

title: reuben rolls
directions: Place cheese in rolls.
Top with corned beef, sauerkraut and Thousand Island dressing.
Wrap each roll in foil.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: john deluxe
directions: Equally divide the ingredients and in alternate layers, make 2 sandwiches.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Take the 2 eggs and milk and beat until smooth.
Dip the sandwiches in the batter and fry until golden brown.
Serve with dill strips and steak fries.

title: sausage roll
directions: Crumble sausage meat; fry with pepper and onion.
Drain grease.
Add Parmesan cheese and tomato sauce.
Bring to boil, then cook over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Place mixture into dough of choice; we use a whole package of crescent rolls pressed together.
Put about half of the mixture longways down center.
Do not put too close to the end.
(Save other half of mixture or freeze for another roll.)
Before closing, put desired amount of shredded Mozzarella cheese over meat mixture.
Fold two long ends together, then place seam side down on cookie sheet.
Pinch under short sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 5 can mexican dinner
directions: Cook the meat and onion.
Add the 5 can ingredients and simmer about 10 minutes.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of the tortilla shells (6).
Pour in 1/2 meat sauce, then the rest of the tortillas and the remaining meat sauce.
Cook for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove and add cheese; heat to melt.

title: broccoli and shells
directions: Steam broccoli; set aside.
Saute garlic in oil.
Add broccoli.
Stir 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook approximately 15 minutes (while shells are cooking).
Pour over 1 pound cooked shell macaroni.
Sprinkle with grated Romano cheese.

title: date nut balls
directions: Combine oleo, sugar and dates in saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook 3 minutes while stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
When cool, shape into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar or coconut.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: blender corn pudding
directions: In blender (or food processor) combine eggs, flour, sugar, salt and one cup milk.
Blend until smooth.
Add drained corn. Blend until almost no chunks remain.
In a 2-quart baking dish, melt butter.
Add blended corn mixture and other cup of milk. Stir with a spoon.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.
Stir twice during the first 20 minutes, scraping sides and bottom of dish.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix
all
together and pour in casserole dish; sprinkle crumbled crackers
over top.
Dab with butter.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: drying tomatoes
directions: Place tomato slices in a single layer on paper towels. Microwave on Low (30%) for 1 hour and 30 minutes, carefully rearranging tomato slices every 15 minutes.
Test for doneness; dry.
Place on paper towels, then cover with paper towels.
Allow to stand until all moisture is gone.
Store in refrigerator, freezer or at room temperature in airtight container.

title: cream cheese (pecan) pound cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Soften butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add flour and salt; beat until combined.
Stir in vanilla and remaining pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, until done.
When done, cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: one pot chicken dinner
directions: In the bottom of a deep pot (6-quart) or a deep casserole dish, place onions and celery and mix.
Put seasoned chicken on top of onions and celery.
Layer sliced potatoes, then mushrooms, then green beans.
In a bowl, mix 2 cans mushroom soup with 1 1/2 cans water and pour over layered mixture.
Place in a 350° oven and cook 1 hour or until chicken is done, if using other cuts of chicken.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place back into oven until cheese melts.

title: mama burgers
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve hot on hamburger buns.

title: sugar-free devil's food cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk, shortening and vanilla. Beat well.
Add boiling water and soda.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: no fail custard pie
directions: Grease pie dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes more.
Let set and cool.

title: tuna and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Place in frying pan with cover, add soup and milk, stir and mix.
Add other ingredients except for grated cheese and mix well.
Cover and simmer slowly until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Can be baked with grated cheese at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: hot rice
directions: In rice cooker, saute onions and pepper in margarine. When they are done, add all other ingredients.
Start cooker.
When bell rings, wait 10 minutes to serve.
Good with barbecue sauce.

title: karen's creamy cheese potatoes
directions: Put into skillet melted butter, potatoes, green peppers, water, salt and black pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring often.
Stir in heavy cream or milk and 1/4 pound grated cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese melts and sauce thickens.
Do not boil.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Cook bacon until just crisp. Add onion and celery and cook until tender. Stir in flour and salt. Gradually add milk.
Cook over low heat until smooth and thickened, about 10 minutes.
Stir often. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Yields 4 servings.

title: good luck bean soup
directions: Soak bean mixture overnight if you want to.
Takes longer to cook them if you don't.
Drain beans and add water and cook 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 cups.

title: dixie relish
directions: Mix vegetables together; cover with the salt and let stand overnight in a crock or enameled pan.
Drain, then add spices, sugar and vinegar and pack into hot sterilized jars.
Put on caps, screwing band tightly.
Process in water bath at simmering temperature (180°) for 15 minutes.
This relish is a splendid filling for mango pepper!

title: white lightning candy
directions: Mix together and put into a 2-quart casserole.
Turn oven on low and melt everything together.
Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and let harden.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta shells.
Drain and run cold water over.
Chop onion, cucumber and tomato; add to shells.
Add olives.
Sprinkle in entire container of Salad Supreme.
Pour over Italian dressing and allow to chill several hours.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain grease off ground chuck.
Chop up onions fine, then saute.
Then put in oven.
Use tomato sauce, brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Add all that to meat.
If you want it hot, use hot beans.
Soak out pinto beans, Great Northern beans, lima beans and peas.
Soak beans overnight, then cook.
Drain water from beans.
Mix together.
Simmer, then cook until done.

title: pizza burgers(makes 9)
directions: Brown meat with onions.
When meat is cool, mix with ingredients.
Fill hamburger buns with mixture and sprinkle with oregano.
Wrap in foil.
Keep in refrigerator if serving later. Heat in
350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
For 18 buns, use double recipe.

title: ranch cracker snacks
directions: Mix dry dressing with oil. Stir until mixed well. Pour over oyster crackers in a plastic container. Keep in container overnight. Toss occasionally. Serve. Keep remainder in an airtight container.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; then add eggs, 1 at a time.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with the buttermilk.
Add flavoring.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oatmeal and buttermilk.
Soak for 1 hour.
Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add oil and egg to oatmeal mixture. Stir in dry ingredients until moistened.
Spoon into muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend.
Pat onto bottom of well buttered 10-inch spring-form pan.
Chill in refrigerator or freezer for 15 minutes.

title: quick orange pineapple salad
directions: Mix drained fruit with coconut and sour cream.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in oblong casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is really great!

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti by directions on box.
Dice tomatoes and green pepper.
Mix all together.
Add Italian dressing and Italian seasoning.
Marinate overnight and serve.

title: irish potato cheese casserole
directions: Melt one
stick
of
butter
and one cup of milk.
Pour over other
ingredients	and mix.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lite "n" easy cheese dip
directions: In medium bowl mix first three ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers, Melba rounds or toast.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and cream cheese in large4 bowl. (Will be frosting consistency) Add milk, pudding and cool whip. Blend well. The mixture will be very thin. Let sit 15 - 20 minutes to thicken. Crush Oreos. Layer cookies and pudding mixture in a bucket. Add silk flowers and serve with a shovel.

title: mom's baked beans
directions: Step 1. Mix first 5 ingredients together in a baking dish.

title: world's best pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers overnight in 2 double handfuls of lime and water.
Next, soak 2 hours in clear water, then add alum and bring to a boil; drain.
Next, add vinegar and sugar.
Now tie a bag of mixed pickling spices and hang into syrup.
Boil for 30 minutes, then can.
Makes about 14 quarts.

title: ginger bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers, melted butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar to form crust.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip together cream cheese, Dream Whip and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Put on top of graham cracker crust.
Spread 1 can of cherries on top and refrigerate.

title: impossibly easy chicken 'n broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle broccoli, 1 cup of the cheese, the chicken and onion in pie plate. Stir Bisquick, milk, salt, pepper and eggs until blended.
Pour into pie plate.

title: dill pickles
directions: Let vinegar, water and salt come to a boil.
Place cucumbers in jar and add alum, red pepper, dill seed and garlic clove in each jar. (May leave out red pepper and garlic.)

title: smoked salmon pate
directions: Combine salmon and next 7 ingredients.
Shape into a ball or log.
Chill for several hours.
Before serving, roll ball in nuts, then parsley and paprika.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: braised red cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in half.
Wash, drain, core and shred.
Melt butter in kettle over low heat.
Add shredded cabbage.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Toss until mixed. Cover.
Cook 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: aveiro mussels(mexilhoes de aveiro)
directions: Wash and scrub mussels thoroughly, rinsing several times to make sure they are free of all sand and particles.
Chop onion; brown lightly in hot olive oil in a heavy skillet.
Add mussels; cover tightly to steam, shaking pan from time to time.
When shells open, take mussels out of pan and remove empty shells, being careful to retain all the juice, which is returned to pan with the shelled mussels.
Add crushed garlic cloves, wine, pepper and saffron, then rice, letting it brown slightly before gradually adding fish broth.
Cook over low heat until rice is thoroughly cooked.
Stir occasionally so that rice does not stick to the pan.
Serve on rye or wheat Melba toast.

title: italian deli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough mayonnaise to make creamy.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Melt chocolate bars.
Whip cream and fold into chocolate. Crush wafers and put into greased pan.
Reserve some for top. Pour chocolate on top of wafers.
Add remaining wafers.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine whipped topping, mayonnaise dressing, pineapple, marshmallows, cherries and nuts. Pack into 8-inch square glass dish. Cover. Freeze several hours or overnight, stirring once after first hour of freezing. Cut in squares. Serve on lettuce. Makes 9 servings.

title: orange carrot cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla, then add orange juice and rind.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add carrots.
Bake approximately 12 minutes in preheated 375° oven.
Ice with frosting made from powdered sugar and orange juice.

title: puffy omelet
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add water and salt.
Continue beating about 1 1/2 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Beat egg yolks at high speed of electric mixer, about 5 minutes or until thick and lemon colored.
Fold egg yolks into egg whites.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom and sides of crust evenly with egg yolk.
Bake on cookie sheet until light brown, about 5 minutes.
Remove from oven. Combine apples, lemon juice, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup brown sugar, 3 tablespoons flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well and spoon into crust.
Mix remaining flour, sugar, brown sugar and butter with fork until crumbly. Sprinkle topping over apples.
Bake on cookie sheet until topping is golden and filling is bubbling, about 50 minutes.
Cool thoroughly on rack about 4 hours.
Serve at room temperature. Serves 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until brown and springs back when touched with fingers.

title: ham and bean chowder
directions: Place beans in dutch oven, cook as you normally cook until beans are just tender. Drain beans, discard liquid. In same kettle, saute onion, celery, and garlic or garlic powder. Add beans and all other ingredients except milk and cheese. Bring to a boil. Reduce to medium heat. Simmer for 2 hours. Remove bay leaves and clove after 1 hour of cooking. Refrigerate overnight to skim fat. Add milk and heat thoroughly. Just before serving, stir in cheese. Serve with cornbread muffins. Serves a crowd for a good cold weather meal.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the apples, pineapple, grapes and celery. Add enough mayonnaise to hold the fruit and vegetables together.
The sweetness of the fruits will decrease the intensity of the mayonnaise. Add chopped walnuts to taste.
Refrigerate until served. Add the sliced bananas just before serving to prevent them from becoming mushy.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients in pie plate and press.

title: salsa dip
directions: Pare, grate and drain cucumber.
Combine all ingredients in food processor.
Serve as is as sandwich or canape spread.
Thin with sour cream to make a dip for vegetables.

title: peanut butter cored apple
directions: Core the center of an apple. Put peanut butter in the middle. Cut apple in circles.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk in a heavy 3-quart saucepan. Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat.
Stir in chips gradually.
Mix until melted. Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Pour into 9-inch greased baking pan.
Cool at room temperature.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours on 250°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, then add oil and water.
Stir in pumpkin.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend in egg mixture; stir well. Add nuts and raisins.
Bake one hour at 325°.
Makes 3 medium sized loaves.

title: strawberry rice
directions: Mix jello according to directions on package.
When set, add rice, granulated sugar and vanilla.
Mix well until blended.
Fold in strawberries.
Whip cream with powdered sugar until stiff. Fold into gelatin mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight. Serves 10 to 12.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Heat milk until tiny beads form around edge (scalding).
In bowl combine 2/3 cup hot milk with sugar, flour, cornstarch, salt and egg yolks with wire whisk until well blended.
Gradually whisk into remainder of hot milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Blend in coconut, butter and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue topping, sealing well at edges.
Sprinkle with coconut if desired. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Blend well.
Serve over block of cream cheese with crackers.

title: christmas cranberry mold
directions: Drain pineapple; save syrup.
Mix jello and sugar; add hot water and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water, lemon juice and reserved syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, cranberries, orange, celery and walnuts.
Pour into 2-quart mold and chill until firm.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and jello.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, then remove from heat. Add cream cheese (may have to blend with mixer).
Melt.
Add water, milk and nuts.
Fold together.
Chill in mold until firm or may use pretty dish.

title: extra cheesey lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion together and drain. Add garlic powder, oregano, salt and pepper. Blend tomatoes in food processor or blender until smooth. Add to meat. Add tomato paste and simmer a few minutes.

title: macaroni-chicken dinner
directions: Cook macaroni and
salt
according
to directions until tender; drain.
While macaroni
is	cooking,
beat	egg
and 2 tablespoons water until
just
mixed.
Dip chicken pieces into egg mixture, then into cheese, coating each piece well.
Brown chicken in hot
oil
in large skillet, a few pieces at a time, adding more oil if needed.
Pour off drippings.
Add tomatoes and stir
well to loosen brown bits in skillet.
Add chicken, onion, green pepper
and
macaroni.
Cover
and	cook
for 45 minutes or until fork-tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jordan's irish christmas cake
directions: Maraschino cherries come glazed in a plastic container.
Fill it up with rum and let sit overnight.
Raisins may be added as well.
Mix all cake ingredients together until smooth.
Add chocolate chips, walnuts and cherries.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
(Use Crisco, not butter.)
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until cake checks done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes; then turn onto plate.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together and shape into balls.
Melt chocolate and dip balls, put on wax paper to dry.

title: mexican turnovers
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together in bowl.
Cut in the shortening.
Add the cold milk.
Stir into a ball, handling like pie crust.
Roll out thin; cut in 4-inch rounds or squares. Place a spoonful of filling on one half of a round.
Fold over, moisten edges and press firmly so they seal.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese and paprika.
Pour into greased crock-pot (greased with margarine).
Sprinkle top with extra cheese and paprika.
Cook on low 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: mexican-rice
directions: Clean rice.
Rinse.
Fry rice like popcorn (no grease, no lard).
Mix and turn for 8 minutes.
Then take off of stove and put in cold water.
Drain.
Add catsup, garlic, salt, tomato, onion and bacon. Cover for 1 hour.

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Mix shortening, eggs and buttermilk.
Add All-Bran which has been soaked in the boiling water for a few seconds.
Add sifted dry ingredients and the 100% Bran.
Store in covered jars.
Will keep in the refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Yields 4 quarts.
One quart makes 18 muffins.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan cheese topping for flounder
directions: Place fillets under broiler for 3 minutes (dark side up). Turn flounder over; spread mixture of other ingredients on top. Broil for 4 minutes.
Good with spinach bread.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine, peanut butter, coconut, pecans and powdered sugar.
Roll into balls.
Dip in paraffin wax and chocolate chips.
Lay on wax paper to dry.

title: fat-free fudge brownies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, salt and sugar; stir.
Add applesauce, egg white, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool to room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: pork loin marinade
directions: Mix red pepper, vinegar, salt, garlic and wine.
Put meat into a marinade pan and pour marinade over meat.
Marinade should cover meat.
If it doesn't, make a small portion with more wine to cover meat.
Soak in refrigerator for 3 days.
Put meat and marinade in 350° oven.
Cook until meat is tender and browned.
Do not change marinade.

title: jello delight
directions: Cook eggs, sugar and butter in a double boiler for about 2 minutes.
When mixture is cooked, add pineapple and chopped nuts. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place graham crackers.
Then, layer the graham crackers and mixture, graham crackers and mixture.
Prepare strawberry Jell-O.
When Jell-O is slightly thickened, pour it over the layers and chill.
After it has set up, top with Cool Whip.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix chowder and cream cheese together.
Puor into oven proof bowl and top with cheese.
Bake 350° for 20-25 minutes.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: crisp gingersnaps
directions: Omitting sugar, mix dry ingredients together in large bowl. Cream shortening and sugar by hand.
Add egg and molasses to shortening mixture and blend.
Stir in flour mixture, blend well together by hand.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in some granulated sugar.
Press lightly.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased sheet in 350° oven.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Combine cake mix and Jell-O; add oil.
Beat in one egg at a time and add frozen strawberries.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with white frosting or whipped cream.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Add all ingredients (juice and all) in a large pot.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture is hot.
Makes a lot of soup.

title: sopaipillas(fried bread)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Cut in shortening, adding enough water to make a dry dough (about 1 3/4 cups).
Let dough stand about 20 minutes.
Roll out on floured board 1/4-inch thick and cut into 3-inch squares.
Deep fry in hot fat until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute the onions and bell pepper in margarine.
Add the rice, consomme, water and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° until rice is done.

title: cathie's cowboy dip
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef.
Drain.
Add Velveeta and Ro-Tel.
Mix well.
Add Cavender's and stir all ingredients. Serve in a chafing dish with tortilla chips.
Cowboys love it!

title: fantastic punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in 2 cups hot water. Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a large pot and cover with water. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, or until potatoes are tender. Drain, but reserve 1/2 c. liquid. Mash potatoes with a potato masher. Add reserved liquid and remaining ingredients. Mash until well blended.

title: pepper-chicken fettucini toss
directions: Prepare fettucini as package directions; drain.

title: mushroom sloppies
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add celery and soup; simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve in hamburger buns.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Drain fruits.
Set juice aside.
Pour cherry juice on softened cream cheese, mix together.
Add fruits and 1/4 cup of juice.
Blend.
Pour into muffin tins and freeze.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake loaf at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stir-fry teriyaki
directions: Partially freeze beef.
Cut on bias into thin strips.
Add oil to large skillet.
Stir-fry vegetables 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove vegetables.
Stir-fry 1/2 the beef at a time for 2 to 3 minutes.
Return all to skillet and toss with sauce.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl; add graham cracker crumbs, stirring with a fork.
Stir in dates.
Shape mixture into 4 (1-inch) balls.
Roll balls in pecans.
Cover and chill thoroughly. Yield:
4 truffles.
Exchange = 1 starch for each truffle.
Fat: 2.2 g. Calories:

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cut angel food cake in small pieces.
Prepare vanilla pudding. Put layer of cake pieces on bottom of large bowl or punch bowl. Layer the pudding, pineapple, bananas, strawberries, cake and Cool Whip, ending with Cool Whip on top.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: This pie does the impossible by making its own crust.
Combined with taco seasoning mix, it's delicious!

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs well and mix in sugar; add milk.
Cook until it coats a wooden spoon. Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: sour cream-raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick; stir in sugar.
Add sour cream, raisins and pecans.
Pour into a 9 inch pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°; lower heat and bake an additional 45 minutes at 350°.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning together.
Spread in bottom of dish.
Layer sour cream on this, then layer guacamole dip over sour cream.
Put layer of chopped onion, then layer of green chilies.
Top with shredded cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: oatmeal-fructose cookies
directions: In electric mixer, beat margarine, eggs, fructose and vanilla until blended.
Stir soda into flour.
Add flour in batches to fructose mixture, while beating, to make a smooth batter.
Scrape sides of bowl often.
On lowest mixing speed, add oats all at once and mix just to combine.
Batter will be stiff.
Remove beater and stir in nuts or raisins, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets that have been lightly sprayed with Pam (or use nonstick sheets).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Cookies have a soft, cake-like texture and will not spread during baking.
Yields about 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish, put vegetables in dish, cut half of oleo stick in chunks and put on top of vegetables.
Soften cheese and put on top of vegetables.
Melt last half of oleo stick. Crush Ritz crackers in plastic bag.
Pour in melted oleo and mix well.
Pour crackers over top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Enjoy!!!!

title: savory chicken and mushrooms
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon of butter, cook chicken 15 minutes or until browned on both sides and no longer pink.
Remove; keep warm.
Reduce heat to medium.
In same skillet in remaining 1 tablespoon of hot butter, cook broccoli and mushrooms until vegetables are tender-crisp and liquid evaporates, stirring often.
Add soup and milk; heat through, stirring occasionally.
Spoon soup mixture over chicken.
Serve with noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stain glass salad
directions: Start with peach pie filling in large mixing bowl.
Add other fruit and sugar and sprinkle liberally with Fruit-Fresh.
Transfer to fruit bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach squares
directions: In 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, melt butter.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat eggs well, then add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add cheese, spinach and onion; mix well. Spoon into baking dish; level and sprinkle with seasoned salt. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Salt and pepper squash to taste.
Melt margarine; mix with stuffing mix.
Pour layer (1/2 mix) in bottom of casserole.
Mix all other ingredients; pour over stuffing mix.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix items together except flour and milk.
Then mix milk and flour together until smooth and then mix all of everything together.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours or until firm and slightly brown.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; season with salt and pepper to taste. Add soup, chilies, enchilada sauce and milk.
Simmer until reduced by half.
Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan with tortillas.
Spoon meat mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cheeses and repeat.
When serving, top each square with a dollop of sour cream.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer the cracker crumbs in a casserole dish.
Place asparagus on top of the crumbs.
Beat the egg with the milk and juice from the asparagus.
Pour over the asparagus and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Heat fat in large skillet with tight fitting cover.
Add onions until lightly brown.
Add chopped meat and cubed beef and brown.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook together for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat margarine and powdered sugar.
Add 1/2 cup granulated sugar and salt.
