Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Chill.
Shape in 3/4-inch balls.
Flatten with bottom of glass, coated with butter, sugar and nutmeg.
Place 2-inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tomato-feta salad with thyme
directions: Combine tomatoes, cheese and green onions in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: deviled chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in 1/4 cup shortening.
Take out chicken and add to shortening 3 tablespoons flour, consomme soup and 1/2 can water.
Mix together mustard, catsup and Worcestershire.
Add to soup mixture.
Add chicken and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: baked orange chicken(working woman, easy!  healthy)
directions: Place chicken breast halves or pieces in a large baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and stir with wire whisk.
Pour orange juice mixture over chicken.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Stir sauce before serving.
Good with rice or noodles.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: snicle doodles
directions: Mix
thoroughly
shortening,	sugar
and
eggs.
Sift together and
stir	in
flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.	Then roll balls in mixture
of
tablespoons
sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon. Place 2
inches
apart
on ungreased cookie sheet.	Bake until light brown
but still soft.
Temperature:	400°, bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen 2 inch cookies.

title: cool whip frosting
directions: Mix together the pudding, powdered sugar and milk.
Let set for 1 minute, then fold in Cool Whip.
Frost cake.

title: crescent delight
directions: Place crescent rolls on bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until smooth.
Put over crescent rolls.
Put second package of rolls on top.
Beat egg white and put over top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage in skillet.
Drain.
Add chili. When chili mixture is hot, add cheese.
When cheese is melted, serve with your favorite chips.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in melted shortening and sugar.
Combine flour and salt; add to the yeast mixture, stirring well.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 2 minutes).
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.

title: fruit soup
directions: Peel the banana and slice it.
Put bananas and oranges in the bowl with the juice.

title: rancho beans
directions: Fry onions and ground beef until done.
Add remaining ingredients and place in casserole.
Bake in 400° oven about 45 minutes.

title: ice cream fudge
directions: Heat the chocolate and ice cream together. Stir in the vanilla and nuts.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan to cool.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream together cheese and butter.
Blend in flour and cayenne. Drop teaspoonfuls of dough on waxed paper.
Wrap each teaspoon of dough around an olive, covering completely.
Bake in oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
(Recipe says it should make 25 balls; I double the recipe and get about 32 to 34.)

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add next four ingredients. Mix lightly.

title: family favorite meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix oatmeal, eggs, soup mix, ketchup and steak sauce. Let stand for 10 minutes. Add ground chuck.
Mix thoroughly. Form in large Pyrex dish.
Take knife handle and create basket pattern on meat. Decorate with ketchup and bake for approximately 1 hour. Great for leftover sandwiches.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large bowl.
Beat for about 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and walnuts. Pour in greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake for about 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and frost with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine bread crumbs and sausage in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings and pour over bread, sausage mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Set in refrigerator overnight or for 12 hours.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes. Let set 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry hamburg, drain grease and add taco mix. Put hamburg mixture in a soft corn shells, placing seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over enchiladas and top with cheeses. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: apple burritos
directions: Lay tortillas flat and distribute pie filling evenly down the center.
Roll the tortillas like a burrito and place in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
In a saucepan, bring the apple cider, margarine and sugar to a boil.
Pour this over the tortillas and bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting the tortillas with the syrup in the pan every 15 minutes.
Serve with a scoop of frozen yogurt.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese fingers
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Then slice crosswise into 1-inch fingers.
Don't cut through bread all the way.
Leave the fingers attached.
Mix cream cheese and dressing mix together and spread on the bread.
Place toppings on bread and broil until brown and bubbly.

title: toffee bars
directions: Break apart approximately 2 packages of graham crackers and place on a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt butter and sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and nuts.
Pour and spread with spatula over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Very quick and easy recipe!

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Melt chocolate squares and add to mixture.
Add eggs and mix well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add half to peanut butter mixture with half of water.
Mix well.
Then add the rest of the peanut butter mixture and water.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in two pans.
Cool.
Melt 6 packages (12 cups) Reese's peanut butter cups in small amount of milk.
Cool and spread between layers and on top.

title: chocolate chip coconut bars
directions: Spread crumbs over melted margarine. Sprinkle evenly over crumbs, coconut, then chocolate chips, then nuts.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over all.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mock peanut butter brittle
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and syrup.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix well. Spread and press in a buttered pan.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together.
Pour over crackers and bake at 275° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs or pork chops
directions: Place ribs in roaster, uncovered, and bake for 1/2 time at 400° (1 hour).
In saucepan, brown onions, sliced in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Pour over spareribs; turn oven down to 350° and bake for 1 hour longer. Baste often (about every 15 minutes).
Serves 4.

title: earthquake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts in pan.
Mix and beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine together.
Set aside.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Pour cream cheese mixture over cake mix.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef; stir in remaining ingredients, except for cheese. Simmer on low heat until hot.
Pour in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: snickers cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directions say.
Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan; pour half of cake mix into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. While baking cake, mix and melt the caramels, butter and milk. After the first half of cake is done, pour this mixture over it, then pour on chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour on the rest of cake mix.
Bake at 200° for 10 minutes, then increase temperature to 350° and bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo or butter until onion is wilted.
Blend flour with mixture.
Pour in milk gradually.
Stir constantly.
Add egg yolks, salt, red pepper and black pepper; cook for 5 minutes.

title: watergate dessert
directions: Mix the pineapple
and juice and all the pudding together. Add the nuts and mix well.
Then add marshmallows.
Mix well.
Add the Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Chill overnight or at least 6 hours before serving.

title: sweet-sour dip
directions: Cook
bacon until crisp, drain on paper towel.	Combine cream cheese,
salad dressing and milk in a medium-size bowl; beat until smooth.
Fold in bacon, chill several hours.
Serve with crackers or crisp vegetable sticks.

title: steak diane
directions: With meat mallet or rolling pin, pound meat to 1/4-inch thick. Spread both sides with mustard.
Over medium heat, warm large nonstick skillet coated with nonstick spray.
Add steaks and cook until done.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
Cover with brown gravy and cook until done.
If extra guests arrive, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all in saucepan.
Cook slowly until mixture is thick. Keep stirring until mixture has no lumps and it is evenly thickened.
Pour into greased baking pan and dot with butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Let cool before cutting.

title: quick chocolate cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool and serve.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Blend well the cake mix, sour cream, oil and eggs.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned peanut brittle
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, heat together sugar, syrup and water.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Boil on medium-high until syrup reaches approximately 250°.
Add nuts.
Continue to boil and stir until it reaches 305°.
Syrup will be yellow brown and peanuts will pop and brown slightly.
Remove from heat and add soda and butter.
Stir well.
Pour into two large greased aluminum foil strips.
As candy begins to cool, pull outer edges to stretch. When cooled, break into pieces.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: *Note:
You may substitute with 2 cups of applesauce.

title: sausage ball appetizers
directions: Mix Bisquick and sausage.
Add melted cheese and mix well. Form into tiny balls and freeze.
Take from freezer, as needed, and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
150 balls or more, depending on size.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix together butter, cream cheese, crisco, and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, then add vanilla.
Mix well and then add the milk.
Pour into a greased 10 tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: amolee's rolls
directions: Mix dry yeast with 1/2 cup warm water.
Dissolve sugar and salt in 2 cups of water and oil.
Add beaten egg.
Combine all together, then add flour, a little at a time.
Mix well.
Cover and put in warm place until double in size.
Knead down and put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Can stay as long as 1 week.
When ready to use, roll dough until about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into desired shape or size.
Let rise in baking pan about 2 hours before cooking.

title: zucchini deluxe
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Cool to touch, then crumble.
Saute zucchini in small amount of light olive oil, along with the sliced onion.
When zucchini is tender, add crumbled bacon to skillet and mix with zucchini and onion.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover skillet and cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Delicious!

title: caramel snappers
directions: To toast pecan halves, spread nuts in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Toast the nuts in a 350° oven about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Combine pork, water, bouillon cube and salt; cover and simmer until tender.
Drain pineapple, reserving the syrup.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thick and bubbly, then remove.
Add sauce to pork.
Stir in pineapple, pepper and onion.
Cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes, until tender-crisp.
Serve over hot rice.

title: fruit fritter batter
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add well beaten eggs and milk. Batter will be thick enough to coat article.
If too thin, add more flour; if too thick, add more liquid.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: apple cider salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of hot cider.
Stir in the raisins; cool.
Add the remaining cider.
Chill until slightly thickened. Add remaining ingredients and chill until set.
Serves 8.

title: coconut cranberry cheese dip
directions: Combine and blend first four ingredients.
Spoon into serving compote dish.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Makes 1-1/4 cup.
Serve with Ginger Snaps.	Double recipe for large group.

title: tia blanca's argentine chimichuri
directions: Mix parsley, garlic, oregano and sweet bell pepper powder well in a 1-quart ceramic or glass jar.
Pour enough oil over so oil saturates and covers the herbs and spices with 1/2 inch of oil on top.
You want 2 parts of oil to 1 part of vinegar, so add 2 large spoons of vinegar to start, salt, and taste.

title: doug's favorite bars
directions: Mix together
all ingredients.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 1 x 1-inch squares.

title: sour cream peach pie
directions: Fill unbaked pie shell with sliced peaches.
Mix sour cream, 3/4 cup sugar and flour.
Pour over peaches in the shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.
Cool well.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Break tuna fish and combine in a bowl with celery, horseradish and mayonnaise using a fork.
Arrange on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with slices of hard-cooked eggs and a dash of paprika.

title: luscious sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large mixing bowl, mash sweet potatoes with butter. Add next 5 ingredients and beat with mixer until mixture is smooth and well blended. Stir in eggs and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool. Refrigerate leftovers. May be served with Cool Whip on top.

title: presidential chicken
directions: Wrap 1 slice of bacon around each piece of chicken.
Place chipped beef on bottom of baking dish.
Put chicken on top of beef.
Mix sour cream and soup; spread on top of chicken. Sprinkle with a little paprika.
Don't salt! Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: maureen's marsella
directions: In an electric skillet or large fry pan, melt butter and add chopped garlic,
Have butcher skin and debone chicken to make 8 cutlets, fresh chicken cutlets.
(No frozen cutlets.)

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together. Place in a buttered baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees. Can use 1 can whole kernel corn or 1 can creamed corn instead of frozen corn.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; slice into small chunks and soak in salty water for about 30 minutes.
Then, drain and cook in fresh salty water until the eggplant is tender.
Drain off the water, then add butter, black pepper, crumbled crackers, onion, cheese, egg and sweet milk.
Mix well and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: peggy's cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Let stand to blend flavors. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook meat and season to taste. Add Ranch Style beans. In a casserole dish, put 4 tortillas. On top of tortillas, put 1/2 of meat and bean mixture and a layer of cheese. Place 4 more tortillas on top of cheese, then the rest of the meat-bean mixture.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in an 8-cup measure.
Add milk and butter.
Do not stir!
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package in 9 x 13-inch or 3-quart baking pan.
Combine 1 large can crushed pineapple and juice with 1 cup brown sugar.
Bring to a boil, then cool (not completely). Poke holes in cake and pour topping over cake.

title: squirrel and dumplins
directions: Quick fry squirrels in bacon grease.
If you prefer, you can just boil the squirrels in chicken broth and leave out step 1. Roll biscuit out very thin and cut into strips.
Cut strips into short segments about 1 x 2-inch.
Drop over into boiling meat broth.
Broth must be boiling to cook dumplings.
After dropping all dumplings, add butter, salt, pepper and milk.
Simmer until thick and creamy.

title: vodka aloha
directions: Put the pineapple pieces into a large glass container.
Insert the lemon grass stalks into the pineapple.
Pour the vodka and the simple syrup over the pineapple and close the container with a tightly fitted lid.
Let rest for 6 days.
Serve chilled or over ice.

title: grandma jeanette's banana pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks, then add milk.
Mix flour and sugar and then add to the egg and milk; put in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until pudding is as thick as desired (pudding is better if not too thick).
Add vanilla.
Layer wafers and bananas in oblong dish with wafers being on your top layer.
Pour pudding over layers.
Let cool for a little while.
When pudding is cool, spoon on Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple banana cake
directions: Stir all dry ingredients together.
Add oil and remaining ingredients.
Mix well but do not beat.
Pour into greased 8-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: bacon bagel snacks
directions: Spread each bagel half with about 1 teaspoon dressing. Sprinkle with bacon and onion.
On broiler pan or baking sheet, arrange bagel halves.
Broil 5 inches from heat 2 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 appetizer servings. Prep.
Time:
20 minutes.
Cook Time:
5 minutes.

title: quick vegetable quiche
directions: In a blender or food processor, mix the onion, eggs, oil, Bisquick, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch Pyrex pan.
This forms the bottom crust.

title: microwave pickles
directions: Mix together and microwave on High 5 minutes. Take out and stir well, then microwave 5 minutes more on High. Cool and eat. Keep in refrigerator.

title: shrimp balls
directions: Drain shrimp; mash with fork until crumbled fine.
Combine with remaining ingredients, saving some cocktail sauce for later. Shape into balls and chill.
When ready to serve, pour remaining sauce over balls.
Serve with crackers.

title: cinnamon-raisin coffee cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until blended.
Combine egg, milk and vanilla; add to flour mixture, stirring until blended.
Set batter aside.
Combine brown sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon and raisins; stir in melted butter.
Set brown sugar mixture aside.
Spoon two-thirds of batter into a greased and floured 9-inch round cake pan; sprinkle with brown sugar mixture and top with remaining batter. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until golden.
Yield:
One (9-inch) coffee cake.

title: double lime punch
directions: In punch bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Serve in punch cups.
Yield:
10 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat the margarine, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy. Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Add nuts, raisins, chocolate chips or coconut, if you like.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into 13 x 9-inch pan; spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling (blueberry and apple are also good) and spread.
Dump dry cake mix on cherry layer and spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over cake and add thin slices of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Check after margarine has melted and add margarine to the dry cake mix.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pasta and vegetable salad
directions: Combine fresh spinach tortellini and next 4 ingredients in a bowl and toss well.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add the shortening, sugar and salt and mix well.
Mix in the flour and let rise for 1 hour in an uncovered container.
Knead about 12 to 15 times, then cut into rolls.
Allow rolls to rise for an additional hour.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute celery, onion and broccoli in oil; add soup and 1 can of water.
Add Cheez Whiz and season to taste.
Add rice and pour into baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange skin side up in large pan. Pour mixture of salad dressing, soup mix and preserves over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender, basting occasionally.
Serve with rice.

title: preacher cookies
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, margarine and milk; bring to boil and cook for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add cocoa, oatmeal, vanilla, peanut butter and nuts (or coconut or coconut and nuts).
Beat together quickly while hot and drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Cool at least 10 minutes before serving.

title: mitzi's fresh apple loaf
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
In separate bowl, mix egg, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients and stir in fresh apples and sliced almonds.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: broiled shrimp and chicken
directions: Alternate chicken, shrimp, tomatoes and green pepper on shish kabob spears.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Broil or place all ingredients in baking dish at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Salt and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Add sliced green pepper, onions and cauliflower when ready to serve.
Do not cook.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook in large saucepan brown sugar, 1 stick oleo and the 1/2 cup of milk.
Cook exactly 2 minutes after it starts to boil around the edges.
Take it off and put the pan in a shallow pan of cool water.
As it starts to cool, add 2 cups of powdered sugar. Beat with an electric mixer for a smoother texture.
If you would like it thicker, add more powdered sugar to your liking.

title: oriental salad
directions: Drain the first 5 ingredients well.
Chop the celery, green peppers and onion.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter. Mix in graham crackers. Add remaining ingredients and mix with your hands and form into a loaf.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool before cutting.

title: crisp onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In shallow baking pan, thoroughly blend first 6 ingredients.
Add potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly. Bake, stirring occasionally, 60 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Yields 8.

title: fluffy cool salad
directions: Place cottage cheese in a bowl and sprinkle with dry jello. Add other ingredients, one at a time, mix well.

title: chris' chili con queso dip
directions: Saute onions and tomatoes with tomato juice and chilies.
When onions are tender and most of liquid is gone, add chunks of Velveeta cheese.
Cook in skillet until cheese melts. Watch it closely and serve with chips when it is creamy.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine cooked, mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla and 1/4 cup butter in large bowl; mix well.
Place in buttered casserole.
Mix brown sugar with flour.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken in broth until tender.
Add Lipton soup mix. Chop carrots and potatoes into bite size pieces and add to broth. Simmer until tender.
Add noodles last and simmer.
Serve with rolls or breadsticks.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed, until mixture holds stiff peaks when beater is raised.
Add sugar, 1 teaspoon at a time; beat well after each addition. Continue beating until mixture holds very stiff peaks.
Lightly fold in peanut butter, just until mixed.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 300° oven for 25 minutes, until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; then set aside.
Beat eggs until light and add sugar gradually.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add dry ingredients alternately with fruit cocktail.
Mix until smooth after each addition.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar and walnuts.
Mix well and sprinkle over cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While still warm, spread with Walnut Topping.

title: boone tavern satin pie(berea, ky)
directions: In electric mixer, whip butter until fluffy.
Sift sugar and cocoa; add slowly to butter on low speed.
Increase speed as mixture is blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Whip on high speed until consistency of whipped cream.
Add vanilla and almond extract and blend.
Pour mixture into baked or crumb crust shell (10-inch) and refrigerate to set at least 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
May be made a day prior to serving. Top with whipped cream and garnish with chopped nuts.
Very rich pie and easily serves 10.

title: mexican stuffed peppers(serves 3)
directions: Cut out stalk and seeds of pepper.
Heat oil in pan and fry onions until soft.
Add mushrooms and rice.
Cook until oil is absorbed.
Take 1/2 pepper (chop finely), broth, chili sauce and salt and pepper.
Stir well and add to mushroom and rice.
Cover and cook until all the liquid is absorbed.
Remove from stove. Stir in chicken (finely chopped).
Mix together then spoon into peppers.
Small dab of butter on each pepper.
Put in baking dish. Add 1/4 pint of water around peppers.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry pecan bars
directions: In medium bowl combine 1 cup flour and 2 tablespoons sugar. With pastry cutter cut margarine or butter into flour mixture until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in half cup of pecans.
Press flour mixture into the bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile combine 1 1/4 cups sugar and 2 tablespoons flour; stir in eggs, milk, orange peel and vanilla.
Fold in cranberries and coconut and remaining chopped pecans.
Spread over partially baked pie shell.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes more or until top is golden brown. Cool on wire rack.
Cut into bars while warm.
Cool.
Makes 36 bars.

title: oven baked meat balls
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Mix together 2 tablespoons vinegar, 1 cup catsup, 1 tablespoon sugar and 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce. Pour over meat balls and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit delight
directions: Cut together the first 4 ingredients until consistency of meal.
Press in pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool thoroughly.
Combine the Cool Whip and cream cheese and spread on cooled crust.
Spread on the fruit pie mix.

title: strawberry mold
directions: Make Jell-O in 2 cups hot water, 1 cup frozen strawberries and 1 cup cold water.
Mix in sour cream; stir.
Pour all into mold. Let it set overnight.

title: country club salad
directions: Carefully wash and chill lettuce.
(Other greens may be substituted or
added.)
Tear into bite-size pieces in a large round salad bowl.
Arrange bacon, eggs, tomato, avocado, onion and cheese separately in pie-shaped sections over greens.
Add dressing just before serving.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake in a well-greased hot pan.
In small frying pan, bake one pancake at a time.
In a large one you can make 3 at a time.
When brown on one side, turn over and brown the other side. Serve hot and well buttered.

title: ham delights
directions: Grind ham and grate cheese.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Spread in Pepperidge Farm buns (small).
Place in bun pan.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Heat for 10 minutes in oven at 400° or until warm.
One recipe makes approximately 30 buns. Excellent to freeze and serve later.

title: man bait meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and shape into loaf.
Mix the last 5 ingredients and pour over loaf.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: donald wade's drop molasses cookies
directions: Cream the oleo and sugars together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon out on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool on pan, then rack.

title: low calorie salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in small mixing bowl; beat until well blended.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: jack clark's hot german potato salad
directions: Bake potatoes and cook bacon until crisp.
Slice and peel potatoes.
Layer potatoes and bacon in bottom of casserole dish. Sprinkle with onions.
In a small saucepan, mix flour, vinegar, brown sugar, celery seed, pepper and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over potatoes; toss gently.
Then put in oven at 325° to reheat for 1/2 hour.

title: virgin mary crab cocktail
directions: Cut up crab and vegetables into small pieces.
Lightly season with celery salt and lime juice.
Add Snappy Tom tomato and chile juice with ketchup to thicken.
Mix in large bowl.
Refrigerate and eat chilled.
Great with soda crackers.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Place pineapple in baking dish.
Mix sugar and flour. Sprinkle over pineapple.
Then sprinkle cheese, then oleo and crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with chow mein noodles just before serving.
Great summer salad.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix with sweet potatoes. Blend together eggs and milk and combine with sweet potato mixture. Pour into prepared pastry. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Lower oven to 350° and continue to bake for 35 minutes or until set.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Yields 6 to 7 dozen rolls.

title: okra patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and flatten into patties.
Brown on both sides and drain on paper towel.

title: 14 day sweet pickles
directions: Let stand for 1 week in a Crock.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Rinse in cold water and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss well and store covered in fridge overnight.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Stir twice during baking.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Mash squash in bowl.
Add butter, eggs, salt, pepper, onion, cheese, milk and bread crumbs; mix well.
Spoon into casserole. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Add oil.
Blend with a fork.
(It should appear dry.)
Beat sugar, vanilla and egg mixture together until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture. Chill 1 hour.
Roll out onto a floured board.
Cut into cookies. Bake 9 minutes at 400°.

title: easy nacho supreme
directions: Brown ground beef; add onions halfway through browning. Combine remaining ingredients.
Serve.
You may add lettuce to make nacho salad.

title: sausage stuffed acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half and remove seeds.
Place cut side down in water (an inch or so).
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle with salt. Cook sausage and onion, drain.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Spoon mixture into cavities and bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Cook everything except vinegar and butter.
When tender add vinegar and butter.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in soup pan.
Add water, bouillon cubes and garlic salt.
Bring to a boil until bouillon cubes dissolve.
Add noodles and simmer 1 minute.
Add broccoli; cook 3 minutes.
Add milk and cheese; simmer until cheese melts.
Do not boil.

title: old fashioned egg salad
directions: In bowl combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in eggs and celery.
Cover and chill.
Spoon 1/2 cup on lettuce leaf per serving.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In skillet, brown meat with pepper and onion; pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients (except buns); bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: pasta marinara
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook onion and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, cooking wine, sugar, oregano and basil.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook pasta; drain and serve with sauce.

title: smothered hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and form into six thick burgers.
Brown burgers on both sides.
Reduce heat and continue cooking until completely cooked, about 16 minutes.
Add 1 (10 1/2 ounce) can of cream of mushroom or any condensed cream soup of your choice.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add a little water if a thinner sauce is desired.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Add peanuts and butter; cook until syrup is brown.
Add soda and mix well.
Spread thin on waxed paper and let cool.
When cool, break in pieces.

title: tamarind water(sauce from thailand)
directions: Combine pulp and water in a small bowl.
Knead tamarind to extract color and flavor.
Liquid will be cloudy and brown. Strain out seeds.

title: cold taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger, heat up refried beans, let cool.
Chop up lettuce, slice avocado and slice onion.
Put all ingredients in dish, pour over salad dressing.
Top with sour cream; keep cool.

title: frozen salad
directions: Combine
first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Beat mayonnaise and
cream
cheese
until smooth; add to fruit mixture. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into plastic mold and freeze.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together in large bowl eggs, pumpkin, oil and water. Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and seasonings. Fold into pumpkin mixture adding raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Fill each half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out dry.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Wrap in foil.
Let stand for 2 or 3 days before serving.
May be frozen.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Cover bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking pan with Velveeta slices.
Drain tomatoes in strainer and discard liquid.
Spoon tomatoes over cheese slices.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes or microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Dip the chips into mixture.

title: world's best green beans(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Preheat the oven to 500°. Lightly oil a large shallow roasting or half sheet pan. Arrange the green beans in a single, uncrowded layer in the pan. Drizzle the oil over the beans and roll until evenly coated. Roast for about 15 minutes, until the beans are well browned, shaking the pan occasionally for even cooking. Transfer the beans to a serving bowl and sprinkle with salt to taste. Serve immediately.

title: easy chicken supper
directions: Cover the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with rice.
Sprinkle salt over rice.
Cover rice with broccoli.
Lay cleaned chicken over top.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over other layers.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Check to see if meat falls off bones.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until barely tender.
Drain well. Add chicken soup, sour cream and onion and mix well.
Sprinkle 1/2 of herb mix on bottom of casserole.
Add squash mixture and sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top.
Dot with butter and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in buttered dish at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sad sam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake in a 9x13in pan at 350 degrees until cake falls in the middle.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix this at medium speed until thick.
Add 3/4 cup chopped pecans.
Mix 3 1/2 cups vanilla wafers and 2 sticks melted margarine together.
Make alternate layers of wafers and creamed mixture.
Put wafers on bottom.
Cream next and so on.
Top with 1 can cherry pie filling and chill overnight.

title: almond fudge topped shortbread
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and salt until fluffy.
Mix in flour. With floured hands, press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips and milk, stirring constantly until chips are melted.
Stir in extract.
Spread evenly over shortbread.
Sprinkle with almonds, press down firmly.
Chill 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into bars.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water.
Cool and cube.
Add all of the ingredients and return to stockpot used.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Return to boil and stir in noodles as directed on package.

title: borscht(soup)
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Add all other ingredients, except tomatoes and cream.
Boil 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook until done.
Add cream and serve.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and water.
Add flour. Mix well.
Add pecans.
Form small balls by teaspoon.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 300° for 20 minutes or until delicately brown.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Preheat frying pan with oil.
Brown chops until golden. Combine garlic, ginger, salt, pepper, sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Pour mixture over pork chops.
Cover and simmer until tender and glazed (50 to 60 minutes).
Turn chops from time to time to avoid sticking and scorching.

title: bread or rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt, water, Crisco and yeast.
Stir in 12 cups flour.
Knead in about 4 more cups flour.
Form into ball.
Brush with melted Crisco.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Knead down and let stand 30 more minutes.
Make into loaves or rolls.
Let raise 2 hours.
Bake rolls at 400° for 20 minutes.
Bread at 350° until brown.

title: banana mousse
directions: Cook sugar and water together in saucepan for 1 minute over medium heat.
Add bananas and cinnamon; cook 3 minutes
over medium heat.
Transfer banana mixture to food processor and blend until pureed.
Chill.
Transfer banana mixture to mixing bowl. Fold in stiff egg whites until well mixed.
Fold banana mixture into cream mixture; mix well.
Spoon into dessert cups and chill before serving.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Mix dressings and seasonings.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: easy date drop cookies
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients together, then add eggs.
Add remaining cookie ingredients.

title: pumpkin raisin cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add pumpkin and oil; stir in cereal just until moistened. Add dry ingredients and stir until combined.
Fold in pecans and raisins.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: jackie pierce's just plain cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add one egg at a time and beat well.
Add flour, mixed with remaining dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Cook in 325° oven for one hour and 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: joyce's banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Add orange, lemon and pineapple juices plus the mashed banana.
Divide into 3 portions and freeze in flat containers.

title: sugar crisp twister
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; set aside.
Mix flour and salt; cut in butter.
Blend in yeast, eggs, sour cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Combine sugar and remaining vanilla.
Roll out half of dough, using vanilla sugar mixture to keep from sticking.
Roll out to 8 x 16-inch rectangle. Sprinkle with sugar and fold into thirds, making layers.
Roll out.
Fold twice more. Cut into strips 4 x 1-inch.
Twist each strip 2 or 3 times.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Repeat with rest of dough.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen twists.

title: mexican-style creamed corn
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine corn, green and red pepper, celery and water.
Cook about 5 minutes or until corn is tender, but not overcooked.
Drain.
Stir in cream cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat through.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 1 hour, until knife comes out clean.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in oil for about 5 seconds (they should be soft).
Roll up tortillas with 1 teaspoon of onions and cheese in the inside.
Place tortillas in a well-greased glass baking dish. Melt butter; add flour until thick.
Add chicken broth.
Cook over medium heat until thick but pourable.
Add sour cream and peppers.
Pour mixture over enchiladas.
Add remainder of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian beef salad
directions: In Season-Serve| container, combine first 3 ingredients. Add beef. Apply seal; invert container to coat beef. Chill several hours.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Drain the tomatoes.
Cook sausage and drain off fat.
Melt cubed cheese in microwave or double boiler.
Add sausage and tomatoes.
Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: dirt cake
directions: Spread 1/2 of cookie crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together cheese, margarine, sugar and Cool Whip.
Combine 2 puddings and milk.
Beat until thickened.
Add to the cream cheese mixture.
Pour over the crust.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill for several hours.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all the ingredients together (except for the nutmeg) and put it into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle a little nutmeg on top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix soups and chicken together in large bowl. Add 1/2 of the sour cream and 1/2 of the cumin and other spices (or to taste). Heat oil in skillet and place tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil just until limp. Drain on paper towel. Lay tortillas in 9 x 13 pan. Spread small amount of mixture on tortilla; top with small amount of cheese. Roll up. Continue doing this, lining all the tortillas up next to each other, seam side down. When pan is full, spread remaining mixture on the top of the enchiladas, topping with remaining cheese. Place in oven until enchiladas are hot and cheese is melted. Serve with jalapenos and picante sauce.

title: crazy corn
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pop popcorn, then melt butter and honey together and stir.
Put popcorn and peanuts in a small bowl.
Pour honey-butter mixture over corn and stir it up.
Pour popcorn in a baking dish and spread it out.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and eat.

title: apple bars
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in butter.
Stir in egg yolks.
Divide mixture in half.
Press half of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Mix together the apples, cinnamon and remaining flour and sugar. Arrange apple mixture over the crust.
Crumble remaining dough over apples.
Brush with the egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and drizzle with powdered sugar.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together with blender.

title: white and green bean soup
directions: Wash and pick over dried beans.
Put them into a large saucepan or kettle with the water and bring to a boil.
Remove from the heat, cover and allow to stand for one hour.
Return to the heat and bring to a boil again.
Reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, for 1/2 hour.

title: mostaccioli casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook mostaccioli noodles until tender.
Put noodles in baking dish and pour milk and egg on top. Mix Ragu sauce with ground beef and pour over noodles.
Layer top with optional salami or pepperoni.
Cover with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian vegetable dip
directions: Mix yogurt, salad dressing mix and onions in small bowl. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, stir in milk until well blended.

title: diabetic peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except cocoa over low heat until melted. Add cocoa.
Put in a small pan.
Chill and cut in 3 servings.

title: fish loaf
directions: Grind Soyameat.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
(Tartex is a stiff mixture, so take a small amount on a plate and mash it with a few tablespoons of the rest of the mixture; repeat until all of the Tartex is blended.)
Press mixture into a flat baking dish. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Cover during the first half of the baking time.
Serve with tartar sauce or a white sauce with parsley.

title: tomato soup
directions: Quarter tomatoes (unpeeled); cook all ingredients except salt, pepper, parsley and juice of lemon.
Pass through a food mill or sieve; season with the remaining ingredients.
Boil and seal into hot sterilized jars; seal.

title: oreo cookie bars
directions: Blend cookies and margarine in small bowl. Sprinkle 1 cup crumb mixture over bottom of lightly greased 8-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with chips, marshmallows and nuts. Top with remaining crumbs. Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and cut. Can double recipe and cook in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry filling for strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and add strawberries.
Spread between and on top and sides of layers. Place in refrigerator or in a cool place.

title: caramel layer or heavenly pies
directions: Cook pie crusts; cool.
Melt butter, add nuts and coconut; brown light and cool.
Cream Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese with mixer and then fold in Cool Whip.

title: ice hot rolls
directions: Scald milk with sugar and Crisco.
Cool and put yeast cake in it.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Stir into milk and set to rise.
After it rises, use flour enough to make a soft dough.
Place in icebox until ready to roll out and cook.
Roll out and let rise.
Grease a pan and put them in the pan.
Cover dough when putting in icebox.

title: mom's quick chicken and dumplings
directions: Over medium heat, slowly add 1 can chicken broth to cream of chicken soup.
After reaching smooth consistency, add remaining 2 cans of chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Divide biscuits into quarters; add to boiling broth.
After all biscuits have been added, let dumplings boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Reduce heat; add cans of chicken.
Remain on low heat until desired consistency.

title: hash brown-ham casserole
directions: Combine sour cream and chicken soup.
Stir in frozen hash browns, ham, cheese and onion.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Serves 50 or 75.

title: lo-cal banana milk shakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Cover and blend on high until smooth.
Makes 1 serving.

title: pear gelatin jam
directions: Combine pears, sugars and pectin.
Bring to boil.
Boil 20 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat; add jello and blend well. Pour into jars and seal.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Crumble one layer of cake in punch bowl.
Mix 1 package pudding with 2 1/2 cups of milk until slightly thickened.
Pour over 1st layer.
Add 1 can drained pineapple.
Add 1 can pie mix.
Add 1 carton Cool Whip.
Add 2nd layer cake.
Mix pudding mix with 2 1/2 cups of milk and add 1 can drained pineapple.
Add 1 can pie filling.
Add 1 carton Cool Whip.
If you like, add chopped nuts and cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in 8-inch dish.
Set in freezer until congealed.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, carrots and onion.
Mix with mayonnaise and sugar.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine corned beef, chopped American cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Alternate in layers in greased 2-quart baking dish with noodles (cooked and drained).
Top with buttered crumbs and bake until heated through at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: With electric mixer, mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and salt. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Let stand several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pecan cake
directions: Soften butter or margarine to room temperature.
Mix butter, eggs and water; beat good.
Then mix all ingredients together. Preheat oven to 450°.
Use one cup of batter per layer.
Bake until layers are done.

title: bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer slowly until beans are very soft, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove bay leaf and bones from kettle.
Remove skin from pork hocks, cut up meat and return meat to soup kettle.
Stir with spoon, mashing about 10% of the beans.
This process thickens the soup and gives it body.
It makes about 15 cups of bean soup.

title: deer jerky
directions: Put strips of meat into sauce and mix well to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.
After 24 hours, put directly onto oven racks on aluminum foil.
Oven temperature should be 200°.
Dry meat for 3 to 4 hours.
May also use dehydrator method according to manufacturer's directions.
This keeps for quite a while in sealed plastic bag.

title: lemon poppy muffins(yield:  30 muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter and 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar until fluffy, scraping bowl often.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream, lemon juice and vanilla; beat at low speed until blended.
Fold in poppy seed and lemon zest.
Fill muffin cups lined with paper baking cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip and pineapple. Put in pie
crust.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup crushed vanilla wafers and 1/2 cup nuts on top.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into balls and cook in spaghetti sauce for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry cool whip cake
directions: Cook cake by directions.
While hot, pour condensed milk on top of cake; let cool.
Then layer with cherry pie filling, Cool Whip and coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: spring brunch bread
directions: You will need Baker's Joy nonstick baking spray.

title: mexicali dinner
directions: Put on Jack stands.
Lay on back with screwdriver shoved in the bottom of big foot.
Twist until satisfied.
Once you have finished, crawl out and get in and mash throttle wide open.
Try to run over everything in sight, then get off and go inside and mess up house.

title: more
directions: Brown meat; add onion and tomatoes.
Simmer.
Put layer of meat, layer of spaghetti, layer of cheese and olives.
Repeat, ending with a layer of olives.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wake-up casserole
directions: Place hash browns in a single layer in a greased 13x9x2 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and ham.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, and mustard.	Pour over ham.	Cover and bake at 350° for one (1) hour.
Uncover, bake 15 minutes longer or until edges are brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: country corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Melt shortening in iron skillet.
Mix corn meal, flour, egg and buttermilk.
Stir in melted shortening.
Pour mixture into hot skillet where shortening was melted.
Bake in oven for 30 to 35 minutes until top is brown and sides pull away from pan.

title: creamy chinese chicken
directions: Place soup and water in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat until bubbly.
Stir often.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook for 10 minutes, or until warm.
Stir often.

title: cracker candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a saucepan; boil 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and crackers.
Beat all together; pour into pan.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel and pre-boil 2 eggplants.
Saute in butter the onion, garlic, peppers, celery and ground beef.
Crumble the toast into the above until all juice is absorbed.
Season to taste with salt and red pepper.
Butter bottom of casserole and pour in mixture. Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup seasoned Italian bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° reduce heat to 350° until top is brown.
Makes a good side dish and also freezes well.

title: ice cream
directions: Mash bananas, then add the lemon and orange juice.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Put in trays.
Stir when slightly frozen, then return to the refrigerator until frozen.

title: mexican mess
directions: Brown
the meat, no salt.
Spread chips, then enchilada sauce in	the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle meat and 1/2
of the cheese over the chips and sauce.
Now make a layer with
the Mexicorn.
Mix both cans of soup together and spread over
the corn.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese over the soups. Now sprinkle the chilies over the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: elegant stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts and dredge in flour.
Put a slice of Prosciutto and a slice of Mozzarella on each piece of chicken. Roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in large skillet.
Add chicken and saute to brown.
Add chicken broth and wine; cover and simmer about 30 minutes, until chicken is cooked through.
In another skillet, saute mushrooms in 1/3 cup butter and 2 tablespoons oil until crisp.
Stir in parsley, add to chicken about 5 minutes before chicken is done.

title: hot collards salad
directions: Heat bacon fat, vinegar and seasonings until very hot.
Add drained collards.
Heat through.
Turn into serving bowl.
Garnish with onion ring slices.
Can easily be doubled.
Great with Hopping John!

title: divinity frosting
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water over low heat, stirring only until sugar is dissolved.
Then boil rapidly, without stirring, to 242° or until syrup forms a firm boil when dropped into cold water. Add cream of tartar, salt and vanilla to egg whites.
Beat until stiff, but not dry.
Pour syrup in a thin stream into beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue beating until frosting will stand in peaks and is of consistency to spread.
Enough frosting for filling, top and sides of 3 layer cake.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.

title: no-fry donuts
directions: Mix as for any bread dough.
Let rise in covered bowl in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Roll out and cut with 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Lay out on bread board.
Brush with melted butter and let rise about 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 425° and bake donuts about 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and brush again with melted butter.
Shake in plastic bag with sugar and cinnamon.
These are fine and no grease like fried ones.
(Try this method on the baby elephant ears.)

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze excess moisture from spinach using a clean kitchen cloth, cheesecloth, or strainer. Combine all ingredients and cook in microwave until creamy. You may need to add water or milk 1 teaspoon at a time until the dip reaches the desired consistency.

title: cheesesteak pockets
directions: In medium skillet over medium high heat, heat oil.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add sandwich steaks and cook 5 minutes or until browned, stirring often.
Drain off fat.
Add soup and mushrooms.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and heat through. Spoon meat mixture into pita halves.

title: orange sherbet party punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Combine juices; add to gelatin mixture.
Chill.
Add ginger ale.
Spoon sherbet into punch just before serving.
Yields 40 servings.

title: pineapple cream dressing for fruit salad
directions: Blend together and pour over fruit salad; chill.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Mix dressing, preserves, and soup mix.
Pour over chicken in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute, until brown, the hamburger and onion.
Drain any remaining grease.
Stir
in
and bring to a boil the remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.	Stir often.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, pudding, butter and 3/4 of the Cool Whip.
Mix very well so cheese will mix up.
Crush the Oreos and line them in bottom of bowl.
Add a layer of cheese mix. Repeat until all is used.
Add remaining Cool Whip like icing and sprinkle top with remaining Oreo cookies.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend well and chill.
Serve with fresh fruit, sliced melons, strawberries, pineapple, etc.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans in water in which they are canned until hot. Drain.
Add onion.
Add vinegar, sugar and water.
Let stay in refrigerator overnight.
Add oleo, heat and serve.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Tear tortillas into small pieces.
Mix everything together in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin soup - i
directions: Brown sausage in olive oil and set aside. Add mushrooms, onions, garlic, celery and sage; brown for 5 minutes and return sausage to vegetable mix. Add wine and cook for 5 more minutes. Add chicken broth and canned pumpkin; simmer for 40 minutes. Add cooked pasta shells and simmer for 5 more minutes. When served, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pork chops and rice(dedicated to my dad, bob snodgrass)
directions: Brown pork chops, slowly, not too brown.
Remove from pan and saute onions.
Mix all ingredients together, except chops and soup.
Place mixture in bottom of flat Pyrex dish and lay pork chops on top.
Mix soup with 1/2 can of water and pour on top. Bake in 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours covered with foil.
Remove foil and bake another 30 minutes.

title: golden west sandwich
directions: Butter bread, removing crusts.
Place on this a thin slice of cheese the same size as the bread, then a slice of cold boiled ham.
Add a second slice of cheese, then a second slice of bread prepared the same as the first slice.
Beat egg and milk.
Slip sandwich into this batter.
Cut into triangles.
Serve on hot plate and garnish with a slice of tomato and pickle.

title: crabmeat and cheese on toast
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Add grated cheese and evaporated milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add crabmeat and mix well. Just before serving, add beaten egg and cook 1 minute.
Serve hot on toast.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Makes 2 pies.
Combine dry pudding, sour cream and crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Dip into pie crust and top with Cool Whip.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with mayonnaise and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients except whipped cream and blend.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: elva's "captain's soup"
directions: Cook chopped onion in oil or margarine in large pan until soft.
Add beef and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring until all pink has left meat.
Add three cans and stir until smooth.
Add frozen vegetables, potato and seasonings.
Bring to boil and simmer for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve as main dish with fresh bread.
Enjoy!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. In a 9 x 13 casserole, layer sausage and bread. Combine eggs, light cream, mustard, mushrooms and salt to taste. Pour
over sausage; top with cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until fluffy. Stir in chocolate. Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each.
Fold in 3 cups Cool Whip. Spoon into pie shell. Chill 1 hour, then top with remaining Cool Whip.
This pie can be made the day before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Fry meat until brown together with onion (until onion gets soft).
Add tomatoes, sauce and spices. Let simmer about 1 hour in 13 x 9 x 4-inch pan.
Put one layer of noodles and sauce.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine orange jello, water, frozen orange juice concentrate, pineapple (drained) and Mandarin oranges (drained).
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until partially set.
Prepare pie filling and instant topping mixes according to package directions.
Mix together; spread over jello and top with grated cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, cheese, milk and salt; mix well.
Add all ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill several hours or overnight. Add additional salad dressing just before serving if desired.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add coconut, raisins, pecans and vinegar.
Pour in two pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water.
Slice into cubes.
Dice and mash eggs with a fork.
Add mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add to potatoes and other ingredients.

title: diet vanilla ice cream
directions: Heat milk just to scalding.
Do not boil.
Stir in gelatin and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into blender; whirl 3 to 5 minutes.
Add evaporated milk; whirl 2 minutes.
Chill.
Pour into freezer and freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
May add 4 ripe pureed peaches or 2 cups fresh strawberries, pureed.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and chopped nuts and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine and drop with spoon on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Note:
Other squash can be used also.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Put into a 1 1/2-quart bowl the flour, salt and butter.
Mix with a pastry blender until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Press mixture firmly into an 8-inch square pan over bottom and halfway up sides.
Drain peaches, saving syrup and arrange them on crust in pan.
Blend sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Mix peach juice, 1 slightly beaten egg and canned milk and pour over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes more or until custard is firm, except center.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: *Put small amount into blender until it turns to powder; measure, then blend.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt corn a bit, then chop a bit (not fine) in processor. Blend into mixture of eggs, milk and butter.
Add sugar, salt, black pepper and Tabasco.
Put into baking dish (greased).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or a little longer.

title: hattie's pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter until light.
Add flour and milk alternately to sugar mixture, beating after each addition. Beat in eggs.
Stir in flavoring.
Place in greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Test center with toothpick.

title: black walnut cake
directions: I use English walnuts instead of black walnuts.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Stir in nuts, coconut and flavor.
Cook in 325° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: microwave chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Melt bark in microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir and heat 30 seconds more if needed to melt the bark.
Dip pretzels into warm bark, then place them on wax paper covered cookie sheets. Once cookie sheet is full, place pretzels in freezer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove and store in covered container in refrigerator. Recipe may be divided in half.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; make walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Boil broccoli and drain.
Put on bottom of dish.
Dot with oleo, salt and pepper.
Boil chicken; debone and cut in chunks. Heat soups and sour cream and pour over top of chicken.
Add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cocktail crackers
directions: Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 20 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken cheese casserole
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken and lightly brown.
Drain fat.
Mix soup and milk together well.
Pour over chicken.
Add frozen broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Boil noodles and serve casserole over them.

title: pineapple delight dessert
directions: Crush the wafers (or use graham crackers) and mix with melted butter.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, saving a few crumbs for top.
Put pan in freezer or refrigerator. Cook egg yolks, crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup sugar in double boiler until thick.
Add jello and cool.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff.
Add the remaining 1/2 cup sugar and fold into the pineapple mixture.
Pour over prepared crust.
Sprinkle with a few crumbs.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: easy company brisket
directions: Line roasting pan with foil; place brisket in center.
Sprinkle with dry ingredients over brisket.
Drizzle catsup over all.
Fold foil to seal securely, leaving air space inside.
Bake at 325° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and cheese casserole
directions: Boil chicken until cooked.
Save 3/4 cup broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces and place in baking pan.
Mix together in pot: broth, cream of chicken soup and Velveeta cheese and heat until blended well together.
Pour over chicken.
Heat butter and water in pan until a boil.
Shut off and mix in stuffing mix.
Put stuffing mix on chicken and place in oven at 350° for 20 minutes. Very tasty!

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: Cut together flour, salt and shortening.
Add egg yolk with enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid and mix well.
Roll out 1/2 mixture to fit in a jelly roll pan.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add spices, then add egg yolks, well beaten.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add alternately with flour.
Add salt, vanilla, nuts and jam.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into large (9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Ice with your favorite caramel icing.

title: don't peek beef stew
directions: Mix altogether.
Put in covered baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: corn and vegetable casserole
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk.
Heat almost to boiling, stirring often.
Add vegetables.
Return to almost boiling point. Cover and simmer on low heat for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Pour all into buttered casserole dish and stir in cheese.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Beat milk and eggs.
Toss spaghetti with mixture to coat. Spread spaghetti on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Top with Ragu sauce, toppings and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut with pizza cutter.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/3 of tomato sauce.
Form loaf or bite size balls.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over loaf and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Bake balls for 45 minutes.
Serve meatballs with decorating toothpicks.

title: mom's brownies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan or microwavable mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant in 1/4-inch slices.
Put them in flour and then into beaten eggs.
Brown in skillet on both sides; set aside. Combine onion and tomatoes.
Add a little sugar or Equal, salt and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes.
In baking dish, first put some sauce, then layer of eggplant, then some grated cheese; alternate layers. Put Parmesan cheese on top.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco.
Add sugar and cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flavoring.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add coconut and mix.
Start in cold oven.
Set at 300° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dessert dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl. Cut in butter.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix until moistened. Bring prepared dessert sauce recipe to a boil.
Drop dumpling mixture into boiling sauce, making 8 dumplings.
Cover; reduce heat to low; cook for 20 minutes.
Do not remove cover for cooking period.
Spoon 2 dumplings apiece into serving dishes, along with a generous helping of warm sauce.
Top with whipped cream or a scoop of vanilla ice cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: seafood stir-fry
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oleo.
Add scallops; cook until done.
Add vegies; cook on low to medium heat until vegies are slightly crisp.
Add shrimp.
Season to taste with Mrs.
Dash, spicy.
Serve over Minute rice.
One half cup rice per serving. Any combination of vegies may be used.

title: strawberry salad and dressing
directions: First Layer:
Combine pretzels, melted margarine and sugar. Spread in an 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut Chicken into serving pieces.
Combine Flour, Corn Meal, Salt, Pepper and Paprika in a large bowl with a cover.
Shake well, so that all is well mixed.
Place two pieces of Chicken in the flour mixture at a time.
Shake so that all the Chicken is well coated.
Put the melted Butter in the bottom of a baking dish (large).
Arrange the Chicken in the baking dish.
In a preheated oven set at 350 bake for 1 hour.
Turn the Chicken several times during baking.
Make sure they are browned even.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, eggs, oil, oleo and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Blend sugar contents with dry ingredients.
Form into walnut size balls and bake on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar or dip bottom of a flat glass in sugar and flatten.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Spoon flour into dry measuring cup.
Add salt to flour.
Bring shortening and water to boil in saucepan over medium heat.
Add blended dry ingredients quickly.
Beat constantly until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball.
Remove mixture from heat. Cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool; cut off tops and fill with favorite filling.
Place top back on and refrigerate.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed.
Add Cool Whip with mixer and then Eagle Brand milk with mixer until creamy.
Layer pudding mixture, vanilla wafers and bananas.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.
Delicious!

title: fillets en papillote
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place each fillet on aluminum foil. Sprinkle each fillet with equal amount of rest of the ingredients. Top each fillet with 1 teaspoon margarine.
Wrap and seal all edges.
Place in baking pan and bake 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings with 225 calories and 5 grams fat.

title: creamy corn
directions: Sift flour into butter in a medium bowl; stir in corn and whipping cream.
Pour into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir; bake an additional 15 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: hawaiian ice
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well with a spoon. Pour in ice cube trays and freeze.
When frozen, put 3 to 4 cubes in glass and add ginger ale.
Garnish with cherry or mint leaves, if desired.
Makes approximately 5 servings.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Mix well and spoon over loaf.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: cheese cake
directions: Chill milk.
Mix Jell-O as directed on box and jell.
Let cream cheese get to room temperature.
Add sugar to cream cheese.
Whip chilled milk with mixer; add Jell-O and cream cheese mixture. Blend all of this with mixer.
Add teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Add graham cracker crumbs on top.

title: fried rice
directions: Rub cooked rice with wet hands so all the grains are separated.
Beat eggs with the 1/4 teaspoon salt.
In a wok or wide frying pan, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat; add green onions and stir-fry for about 30 seconds.
Add eggs and stir and cook until soft curds.
Remove from pan.
Add carrots and peas; stir-fry for 2 minutes and set aside.
Heat the remaining 2 tablespoons oil in pan; add rice and stir-fry for 2 minutes to heat through.
Stir in soy sauce and shrimp, chicken or pork (choose only one).
Add eggs and fold in until they are in small pieces.
Season with salt.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients; add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla into small balls (about 1 teaspoon dough). Roll in granulated sugar; flatten with a fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: delicious artichoke dip
directions: Mix all 4 ingredients together in a baking bowl.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Serve hot or warm.
Must serve with Fritos brand corn chips.
Always the first dip to finish!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and salad oil. Beat in eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a greased pan.

title: old fashion molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add eggs and molasses.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Beat together the egg yolks, sugar, vinegar, butter, salt and cayenne pepper.
Put the mixture into a saucepan and stir until it boils.
Then stir in 1 cup cream.
Let come to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over cooked cabbage.

title: sausage strata(can be prepared ahead - good for christmas morning)
directions: Day
before
serving
strata, grease 12 x 9-inch baking pan. In large skillet, saute sausage and pepper until sausage is
well browned.
Drain
off fat.
Stir in mustard.
Arrange bread in bottom of pan.
Top with sausage and cheese.

title: asparagus dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours to blend flavor.
Serve with chips, crackers or vegetable dipper.
Serves 12.

title: conversation dessert
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and dissolve. Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add whiskey very slowly.
Beat in sugar and lemon juice.
Stir gelatin into egg mixture and chill a short time.
Whip the cream and fold into chilled egg mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into egg mixture.
Line sides and bottom of tube pan that will separate or any other 8-inch pan with the split ladyfingers.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into pan and put a layer of ladyfingers, then pour rest of mixture on top. Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Top may be decorated before serving, if desired.

title: melt in your mouth rolls
directions: Combine scalded milk, sugar and salt; stir until sugar dissolves.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine yeast and milk mixture; add butter and eggs and mix well.
Add flour.
Let rise until double.
Work down.
Make into rolls.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Makes two dozen.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs, parsley and pepper and set aside.
Cook lasagne noodles in oil, then layer in foiled lasagne pan.
Start with sauce (store bought or homemade), then the layer of Ricotta mixture.
Then layer of sauce, then noodles, Ricotta, then sauce, then layer of Mozzarella cheese, then lasagne noodles and top with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered with foil.
Remove foil for 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 2 cups crushed corn flakes or potato chips, or crackers can be used mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine.
Bake 40 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: mrs. tripp's ham, and pickle appetizer
directions: Dry pickles well.

Spread cream cheese on pickles, one at a time, making sure layer of cheese is as even as possible. Starting with the short end of one slice of ham, roll ham onto pickle with cheese as tightly as possible.
Wrap each lightly in wax paper.
Cut each "pickle" into rounds about 1/2-inch thick just before serving.

title: tomato salad
directions: Slice tomatoes and place in medium-sized bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over tomatoes.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Drain tomatoes and serve on a bed of crisp greens.
Serves 4.

title: date balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan; set aside. Beat
cup
sugar and eggs until fluffy.
In another bowl, combine
flour,
baking
powder
and
salt.
Add
dry ingredients to the sugar-egg mixture and blend.
Fold in dates and nuts. Spoon into prepared pan.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a shallow bowl combine cornflakes, basil, garlic powder, pepper, salt and oregano.
Dip chicken in egg, then in crumbs.
Place chicken on a rack in a baking pan. Drizzle with butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking powder; stir in nuts.
Put 1/2 dough into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pat down and spread apricots on top.
Add remaining dough by spoonful and spread with fork.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grandma leap's sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, egg and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or just lightly browned on bottom.

title: no banana pudding
directions: With mixer, beat milk and pudding until thick.
Use whisk to fold in sour cream and Cool Whip until well blended.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with wafers; top with mixture.
Repeat with wafers, then mixture until gone (should be 2 layers of each).
Top with crushed wafers.

title: mexican pinwheels
