directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread on shells.
Drain vegetables on paper towels and sprinkle on next.
Roll and slice.

title: strawberry and cream bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and strawberry extract.
Add lemon juice, then eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with preserves or jam and sour cream.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending well.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Chill and freeze.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in oil until soft.
Stir in tomatoes, breaking up chunks.
Add water and other ingredients, except macaroni and beans.
Cover; simmer for 25 minutes.
Add macaroni; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Stir in beans and liquid.
Cook, covered, for 5 minutes, or until vegetables and macaroni are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Soup is thick.
Serves 4 generously.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Add 1 cup of crushed corn flakes.
Mix well and pour into oiled casserole dish.
Mix remaining cup of corn flakes with melted butter and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Add chopped parsley.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place turkey in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with potatoes, peas and shredded carrot.
Melt shortening in frying pan.
Add onion and saute until browned.
Add celery and green pepper.
Saute for 2 minutes.
Spoon onion mixture into center of casserole and stir lightly.
Add water to casserole.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer or until browned on top.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a heavy skillet.
Add celery, onion and green pepper; simmer until tender.
Add broth, rice and seasoning.
Stir to mix.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lollipop sugar cookies
directions: You will need 24 to 30 flat ice cream sticks and assorted decorations (jimmies, red hots, etc.).

title: fudge, cocoa
directions: Thoroughly combine dry ingredients in a heavy 4-quart saucepan. Stir in milk. Bring to a

bubbly boil on medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil without stirring to 234° (soft-ball stage). Remove from heat. Add butter or margarine and vanilla. DO NOT STIR! Cool at room temperature to 110°. Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss. Quickly spread in a lightly buttered dish. Cool. Makes 3 dozen squares (36 servings).

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased skillet (iron) and bake.
Or pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 375° until browned.

title: banana split pie
directions: Blend together cream cheese and sugar.
Spread in bottom of pie crust.
Drain pineapple and then spread pineapple on cream cheese mixture, then bananas and Cool Whip.
Decorate with cherries and nuts.

title: italian fritatte
directions: Mix zucchini, onion, pepperoni and Bisquick together, then mix eggs and cheese with seasonings.
Now combine all ingredients. Bake in Pyrex dish approximately 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat until light.
Stir in bananas. Sift flour and soda together; mix into batter.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour batter into a well greased pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: letter pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. Add honey and salt.
Then add flour and knead.
Roll pieces and form letters on wax paper.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.

title: my sister's potato salad(low-fat)
directions: Stir pickle cubes, potatoes, onion, celery and chopped egg whites together in a large bowl. Combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and celery seed in a small bowl. Stir until well blended. Pour this dressing over potato mix. Stir all ingredients well. Chill and serve.

title: bacon and cheese oven omelet
directions: Cook bacon.
Drain.
Chop 4 slices (leave rest whole). Arrange cheese in bottom of buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add chopped bacon.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 45 minutes, divided.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix sugar and pineapple on stove; boil 3 minutes.
Add jello. Stir thoroughly after removing from stove.
Let cool.
Add nuts, apples and celery.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator, covered, overnight or until well chilled.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Boil and cool.	Add vanilla.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In a bowl, mix undrained pineapple with dry pudding mix.
Stir in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Pour into serving dish.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: ho-bo dinner
directions: Press ground meat into bottom of a large piece of heavy foil. Slice carrots thin on top.
Slice potatoes across thin.
Slice onion on top, then season to taste.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° or until done.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix the milk and corn.
Add dry ingredients.
Then add shortening and beaten eggs.
Fry until brown in a hot frying pan.

title: quick turtles
directions: Arrange pecans in clusters, 3 or 4 halves, 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Top each cluster with 1 caramel.
Slightly flatten.
Bake at 300° for 7 minutes or until softened.
Remove to waxed paper.
Flatten caramel with spatula; top each caramel with 1 milk chocolate piece from bar while still warm.
Spread chocolate when melted.
Refrigerate a few minutes until chocolate hardens. Yields 4 dozen turtles.

title: stumphole cake
directions: Melt butter. Blend in dry cake mix, pecans and coconut. Spread into ungreased oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Set oven at 350° and bake for 40 minutes.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add Jiffy muffin mix and pour into the baking dish.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and salt, stirring constantly, until clear.
Add jello and mix well.
Cool and add berries. Frozen berries may be used, but use 3/4 cup sugar instead of 1 1/2 cups.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: best ever fruit cake
directions: Melt the marshmallows with the milk in a double boiler.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and mold in tube pan that has been oiled with Wesson oil.
Keep chilled.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine baking mix, eggs and milk in mixing bowl; blend well.
Turn dough out onto surface lightly coated with baking mix and knead gently about 10 times.
Roll or pat into a 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread with butter to within 1/2-inch of edges. Combine sugar and cinnamon evenly over dough.
Roll up jelly roll style and pinch seam together.
Place in pan seam side up and bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Drizzle icing made of confectioners sugar, water and vanilla over warm bread.
Best served warm.

title: uncle carroll's fried rabbit
directions: Adult rabbits should be parboiled.
Soak in cold water with a small amount of salt for 2 hours. Put in a pot of cold water and boil for 30 minutes.
Pour off water. Add hot water along with 1 sliced onion and 1 teaspoon of pepper.
Cook until tender. Remove from water, drain, season with salt and roll in flour in hot grease.
One rabbit usually serves 4.

title: gooey chicken
directions: Flour chicken pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix the soup, water and margarine until melted and pour over the chicken. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Baste occasionally.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium size bowl.
Add lemon juice and seasonings to taste.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix in separate bowl.

title: guacamole
directions: Split avocados in half; remove seed.
Scoop out the fruit; mash with fork.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serve as dip for corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Mix all cream soups, rice and water together.
Pour mixture in baking dish, greased with mayonnaise.
Then put uncooked skinless chicken in.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter. Combine soup, cheese, mustard and vinegar; leave on heat only long enough to heat through.
Layer in 9 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan the broccoli, eggs and cooked mixture, ending with mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and top with French fried onions.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: marinated crab claws
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over crab claws.
Marinate for 8 to 24 hours.
May want to drain before serving.

title: barbecue beef roast
directions: Bake roast until done.
Save juice.
Cut up meat and simmer for 1 hour slowly.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons butter with 2 tablespoons flour.
Mix that combination with 1 1/2 cups sour cream, minced onion, salt and pepper to make sauce.
Grease a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Layer, starting with beans, then sauce.
Next put cheese and finish with 1/2 cup of crumbs with 2 remaining tablespoons of butter and paprika. Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: overnight breakfast
directions: Layer cubed ham, cubed bread and shredded cheese in large greased cake pan.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over layers. Pour melted margarine or butter over top.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix well; pour into well greased (or use Pam) pie dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool and serve.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat over to 300°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Using a 9 x 13 pan, layer the noodles, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese; repeat.
Then top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: march madness tomato soup
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over medium-low heat and minced shallots.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Add tomatoes, cover and cook 15 more minutes.
Place tomato mixture in container or electric blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add milk, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Blend for 5 seconds. Return tomato mixture to pan and cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with oregano and serve with crackers.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple juice in large boiler.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat in eggs.
Add to pineapple juice and cook until thickened.
Add cream cheese (cut in small pieces) and stir until melted.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour into casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Cook at 400° until hot and bubbly.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Serves 2.

title: peanut butter fudge ice cream topping
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar and water.
Stir and cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, margarine and peanut butter.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.

title: tangy broccoli salad
directions: Toss broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion and cheese.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Add to vegetable mixture.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix corn, lightly beaten eggs, salt, pepper, melted butter and milk together.
Place in buttered baking dish, cover with cracker crumbs and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a slow oven for about 1/2 hour or until firm.

title: old-fashioned molasses taffy
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
In it, combine sugar, water, molasses, butter or margarine and corn syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Continue cooking to 265° (hard ball stage) without stirring (mixture should boil gently over entire surface).
Pour onto a buttered platter or shallow baking pan.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until easy to handle.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain and put in 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix tomato sauce with water.
Mix spices, pour over hamburger, then cooked macaroni over this.
Spread cheese, then pepperoni. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dessert
directions: Break up angel food cake in rectangular pan.
Prepare Jell-O as directed.
Put on top of cake.
Prepare pudding as directed. Put on top of Jell-O. Refrigerate. Add Cool Whip before serving.

title: sweet and sour pork or chicken
directions: Cook carrots in 3-quart casserole on High for 5 minutes in oil, covered.
Add onion, bell pepper and meat.
Cook 5 minutes covered. Mix 1/2 cup pineapple juice with cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Add sauce mix to meat and vegetables.
Add pineapple and cook covered for 10 minutes on High, stirring several times.
Serve over cooked rice.
Delicious!

title: orange sherbet torte
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces and put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Don't need a whole big cake.
Scatter mandarin oranges on top of cake.
Mix following and put over top:
jello dissolved in hot water.
Immediately add orange sherbet and stir to dissolve, then add Dream Whip that has been prepared as directed on package.
Add a dab of cream on each piece or a few nuts.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pan.
Brown and serve.

title: crumpet for open face crab sandwich
directions: In large bowl,	combine
flour,
salt, sugar and yeast. Mix well and slowly add
water, milk, butter and eggs. Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Cover
and
let double in size. Fry in hash brown rings on hot griddle, brown on each side.
Makes approximately 12 crumpets.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, chillies and cheese.
Fry tortillas in oil.
Fill each with about 2 tablespoons of the mixture and roll. Pour the rest of mixture over the enchiladas and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, covered with foil.
Serves 8. Happy eating.

title: potato stuffing casserole
directions: In skillet saute celery and onion in butter until done.
Add stuffing mix and stir until lightly browned.
Stir in mashed potatoes and sage, parsley salt, pepper and milk.
Mix well.
Spoon into a greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Dot with remaining butter. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy nachos
directions: Melt Velveeta over low heat.
When melted, add chili and salsa; heat thoroughly.
Arrange chips on plates and pour sauce over them.
Top with olives and onions.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: spareribs and kraut
directions: Brown spareribs in broiler; season.
Place ribs over kraut in a baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and onions until tender.
Drain off water.
Mash coarsely with fork.
Salt and pepper.
Add corn, milk, wine and the seafood.
Cook until hot.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Coat crust with egg yolks and bake at 350° for 5 minutes and cool.
Mix condensed milk and lemon juice; blend well.
Add cherries, nuts, whipped cream and pineapple.
Mix well and fill crust; refrigerate overnight.

title: nine day - cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, bell pepper and onion. Stir in 2 cups of sugar. Combine salad oil, vinegar, celery seed and 2 tablespoons sugar and bring to boil. Add 2 mixtures together; cover and put in refrigerator. Can do ahead.

title: burnt sugar icing
directions: Put three cups of the sugar and the milk in a saucepan; heat to boiling point.
Put remaining cup of sugar in an iron skillet over low heat; stir as sugar melts and becomes a light brown.
Remove skillet from heat and slowly pour in the sugar-milk mixture from saucepan, stirring all the while.
Return to heat and cook until a small dab of the mixture forms a soft ball between the fingers when dropped into cold water.
Add margarine, vanilla and salt; allow to stand for five minutes.
Beat until stiff enough to spread on cake or use as candy.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind together fruits, add sugar and nut meats and chill.

title: hard candy
directions: Bring sugar, water and Karo syrup to a boil at 300°.
Remove from heat and add flavoring.
Pour onto cookie sheet and let cool. Cover with confectioners sugar, then break into pieces.

title: baked quail
directions: Season quail inside and out.
Combine mushrooms, bread crumbs, salt and pepper; saute in butter.
Stuff quail with this mixture. Make roux by browning flour in oil.
Add stock, onions and parsley to roux and cook a few minutes.
Place quail in baking pan and pour sauce over quail.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until tender, basting frequently.

title: dixie biscuits
directions: Mix yeast in the cold water, add the cup of potato water, then add egg, sugar, salt, shortening and mashed potatoes.
Mix well. Then add flour to make a stiff dough, by stirring with spoon.
Set overnight in refrigerator.
Make out in rolls, let rise, cook in 425° oven until brown (about 15 minutes).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Simmer	zucchini
in
very
little
water until tender. Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning
and
garlic
salt.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Drain squash and
add to tomato mixture.
Turn into a 2 quart casserole
and sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a
375°	oven until heated through.
This can be made ahead and refrigerated, then reheated in oven.

title: sweet and sour carrot salad
directions: Peel and cut carrots in chunks.
Cook until tender.
Drain. Mix all other 6 ingredients and cook in boiler until it bubbles. Pour over carrots and let sit overnight.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 8 or 9-inch pans.
When cool, cut into 4 layers.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Frost cake.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together and fry.

title: oatmeal nut bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar and shortening. Stir yeast mixture into cooked oatmeal.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; beat well.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in size, about 1 hour.
Add nuts and salt.
Stir in remaining flour or enough to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until double in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into 2 small loaves.
Place in 2 well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Let rise to top of pan or until double in size.
Bake in preheated hot oven (400°) for 45 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Blend sugar, flour, tapioca, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into apples until well blended.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Cover with top crust; seal edge and cut 4 slits in the center of top crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for another 45 minutes.

title: leigh's brownies
directions: Mix oil and cocoa.
Add sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Mix in nuts (if desired).
Pour a small amount of oil in 8 x 8 baking pan to coat bottom.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Throw in pot. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Can add can of chicken.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Make pudding and set aside.
Line 9X13 baking dish with crackers.
Cover with layer of pudding.
Alternate layers of pudding and crackers ending with pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: baked chicken bonne femme
directions: Sprinkle inside of chicken with 1 teaspoon salt and thyme. Place parsley, celery tops and yellow onion in cavity of chicken. Tie legs together, then to tail.
Place the chicken in heavy casserole with tight fitting lid.
Dot with butter.
Cover; bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Add white onions and potatoes; sprinkle with remaining 1 teaspoon salt.
Add sherry.
Cover; bake 30 minutes longer.
Remove cover; bake until chicken and vegetables are browned and tender, basting frequently with juices in casserole.
Serve sprinkled with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken geraldine
directions: Place thawed artichokes on the bottom of a glass baking pan. Top with chicken breasts, salt and pepper. Cut bacon strips in half and lay on top of chicken.
Pour on vermouth and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Sprinkle chopped tomatoes and Cheddar cheese on top after bacon is brown and cook an additional 15 minutes.

title: portuguese soup
directions: In large skillet boil soup bone and meat and onion for about 1 hour.
Add cabbage and potatoes.
Boil until potatoes are cooked. Add kidney beans when soup is done.
Serve with Portuguese bread.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and egg yolks well.
Add pecans, raisins and coconut.
Beat egg whites; fold in mixture.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour.

title: banana split crumb cake
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar and graham cracker crumbs. Press into 2-quart oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes and cool completely.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar. Spread over cooled crust.
Slice bananas over cheese mixture. Spread pineapple over bananas.
Add cherries and chopped pecans. Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill at least a couple of hours before serving.
Serves 10.

title: georgian spinach souffle
directions: Make a white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and pepper.
Add process cheese spread; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in well drained spinach, bacon and onion.
Gradually add slightly beaten egg yolks; cool.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold spinach mixture into egg whites; pour into 2-quart souffle dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve immediately. Yields 8 servings.

title: rugelach
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Cut dough into 4 pieces.
Use one at a time and keep remainder of dough in refrigerator.
Press dough into 1/4 of nut mixture.
Press to 10-inch circle.
Cut into 12 pie shaped pieces.
Place 3 raisins at the wide end of each piece.
Roll from wide to narrow, forming crescent shape.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet right away and cool on rack.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: domino cookies(yield: 36 cookies)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: five-hour stew
directions: Combine ingredients and put into a roaster.
Bake in slow oven for 5 hours at 250°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat 1 egg white stiff.
Fold into mixture of other ingredients.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in water. Add blueberries. Bring to boil. Simmer until clear and thickened, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice and rind.

title: omelet for two
directions: Place butter in a 9-inch microproof pie plate. Cook on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Combine eggs, water, salt and pepper.
Beat lightly with a fork.
Pour into pie plate. Cover with waxed paper and cook for 4 minutes or until center is nearly set.
Let stand, covered, 1 to 2 minutes. Fold in half and serve immediately.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix apples, sugar and nuts.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add dry ingredients to apple mixture.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Stir.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Melt 4 squares of chocolate with stick of margarine and sugar. Cool (approximately 3 hours).
Add the rest of the ingredients. Make into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes only.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: polynesian swiss steak
directions: In a small bowl, mix the undrained pineapple, tomato sauce, soup mix and mustard.
In 3-quart casserole, alternately layer meat and sauce. Cover and microwave at Medium for 30 to 40 minutes, rearranging meat after 40 minutes or until tender.
Be sure meat is always covered with sauce throughout cooking time to prevent overbrowning.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine the first four ingredients and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Garnish with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: banana bread(cake pan size)
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday peas
directions: Drain mushrooms. Cook peas until tender. Drain peas after cooking. Cook mushrooms and onion in butter until soft. Add drained pimento; heat thoroughly. Add peas last.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Using hands, mix in the lard until thoroughly mixed with no lumps.
Store in an airtight container.
Add milk when ready to use.
May double recipe.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: If you use 1 1/2 pounds of ground beef, use 2 tablespoons of oregano and garlic salt.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix all together (do not brown beef).
Put into a covered 2 quart casserole.
Bake for 3 hours at 325°.
DO NOT OPEN THE CASSEROLE WHILE BAKING.
Serves 6-8.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients; put in greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat milk.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Beat eggs in separate dish; stir in sugar and salt slowly.
Stir in milk mixture, then nutmeg, vanilla and butter. Bake 75 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chipped beef log
directions: Soften cream cheese in large bowl.
Add the Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Chop up the chipped beef and add to mixture.
Next chop up the scallions including stems and leaves and add to mixture.

title: groovy butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg together by hand.
Pat in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch glass pan sprayed with Pam or Baker's Joy. Ingredients will look like dough.
In another bowl, mix with mixer cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour evenly over top of first ingredients.
Bake approximately 1 hour or until top gets golden brown in 350° oven.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Stir in chips.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: microwave cranberry sauce
directions: In 3-quart casserole, stir together, sugar, water and cranberries.
Cover and microwave at High 18 to 20 minutes, stirring every 6 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: coconut-cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet. Add coconut. Stir constantly over low heat until golden brown. Spread coconut on absorbent paper to cool.

title: pork and bean casserole
directions: In a deep baking dish, add ground beef, a layer of thinly sliced potatoes, some onion, can of pork and beans, another layer of meat, potatoes, onion, pork and beans and can of tomato sauce or catsup, mixed with a little water.
Pour over the top.
Cover with lid or foil and bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.
Boil potatoes a few minutes before mixing will reduce baking time.

title: olive-oregano relish
directions: In a small bowl, cover the currants with the boiling water. Let soften about 5 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Mix together flour, salt, nutmeg, cloves and allspice. Mix soda well with the buttermilk.
Add these two mixtures to the creamed shortening and sugar alternately, starting and ending with flour mixture.
Add jam and nuts.
Pour into tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fig cake
directions: Combine egg, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl. Beat with spoon or low speed of mixer. Add oil and flour. Blend. Add figs to stiff batter.
Pour into baking pan which has been oiled and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cut in squares and serve warm or cool.
If plain flour is used, add 1 to 2 teaspoons soda.

title: pretzel salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix together pretzels, 3 tablespoons powdered sugar and margarine.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon crisp; crumble.
Remove skillet from heat; combine 1/3 cup bacon drippings with next 5 ingredients.
Heat and stir until thickened.
Add potatoes, onion and bacon; toss and heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, peanut butter and sugars.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: mexican dorito casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions, adding salt and pepper to taste. Drain grease.
Combine all other ingredients except Doritos and cheese and simmer until everything is cooked together.
Take 9x13 inch pan, put Doritos in bottom of pan, pour meat mixture in and put cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese is melted.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in 6 cups water for 5 minutes.
Add oleo and cheese.
Add egg, Tabasco and salt.
Bake for 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake white cake mix.
Poke holes in cake with a fork.
Add 2 cups boiling water to the 2 packages of jello.
Stir well.
Pour over cooled cake.
Ice with Cool Whip.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and crushed pineapple.
Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: russian tea *
directions: Squeeze oranges and lemons and put juice aside.
Boil rinds, cloves, sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Add to tea.
Add juice when mixture cools.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling in 2-quart baking pan or bowl.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Drizzle melted margarine over top and sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake in 375° oven until done, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef and pork tacos
directions: Brown, sausage, ground beef and spices in skillet. You can also add chopped onions and green peppers to the mixture, if desired. Serve on hot tortilla with tomatoes, lettuce, cheese, onions, hot sauce, sour cream or whatever you like on tacos.

title: pressed chicken(recipe from the 20's)
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Cover with water and simmer until falls off bone.
When 1/2 done, season highly with salt, pepper, celery salt and 1 onion, stuck with 3 cloves.
When done, remove all skin and bones and shred meat into good size pieces.
Boil the gravy down to one cup.
Moisten the meat and pack in layers in a well buttered mold, arranging slices of eggs on each layer.
Cover with plate and put weight on it.
Serve next day with lettuce.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Pour drained veg-all in a 9 X 13 baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over veg-all. Mix onion, celery and mayonnaise together. Spread this over the cheese. Combine crushed ritz crackers with melted margarine. Sprinkle on top of casserole and bake at 350 for 30 to 35 minutes or until celery and onions are done.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon crisp (drain on paper towel) and set aside to crumble over top.
Brown ground chuck with onions (drain).
Drain beans and combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Sprinkle top with bacon and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: pickle roll-ups appetizers
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and onion. Spread mixture over each slice of bread.
Place dill pickle on each slice; roll up and place seam side down in airtight container.
Chill overnight.
Slice into bite size pieces.
Serve with crackers, etc.

title: purple salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in the Cool Whip and most of the cherry juice.
Add cherries, pineapple and nuts.

title: one-step stacked enchiladas
directions: Layer the beef, then 6 tortillas, chili beans, grated cheese, onion and 6 tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the chicken soup and the Ro-Tel tomatoes (chop up the tomatoes) and pour over the top of layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bologna and carrot sandwiches
directions: Grind bologna and carrots in meat grinder or food processor. Mix with mayonnaise.
Makes 4 to 5 sandwiches.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish, mix bread, ham and cheese.
In a bowl, beat eggs until foamy and add milk and mustard.
Pour over bread mixture.
Drizzle butter over all. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinade for beef
directions: Mix well and pour over meat.
Turn often.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Chop/dice tomatoes.
Add beans, corn, spinach and spices. Simmer.
Cook spaghetti and drain, then chop up noodles and add to sauce mix.
May serve hot or cold.

title: jello salad
directions: Put Cool Whip in large bowl.
Sprinkle jello crystals over top and stir in.
Add cottage cheese and stir in.
Then add pineapple and strawberries.
Will set up in a few minutes but does best set overnight in refrigerator.

title: hot hominy
directions: Mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, crumbs and corn.
Add salt and pepper. Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheesecake
directions: Grease 1 (9-inch) spring-form pan (use soft margarine).
Dust with crumbs, leaving layer on bottom of pan.
Put Ricotta cheese into large bowl with cream cheese.
Beat on high speed until well blended and creamy.
At high speed, add sugar, then eggs.
Reduce speed to low; add cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well. Add margarine and sour cream.
Blend on low speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until firm around edges.
Let cake stand in oven 2 hours.
Make sure the oven is turned off.
Remove and cool completely on wire rack. Remove sides of pan.
Make 12 servings.
Top with fresh fruit or canned pie filling (chilled).
Can be frozen without topping.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Core and quarter the apples.
Remove all seeds.
Cook apples in water in kettle until tender.
Cool and put apple sections in blender to make a smooth pulp.
Put apples back in kettle and add pectin, sugar and spices.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes. Stir constantly as this mixture will burn easily.
Blend in 2 to 3 drops of red food coloring.
Store in jars in refrigerator or put in jelly jars topped with melted wax.
Very good on toasted bread.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Stir and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and mix powdered sugar in until right spreading consistency.

title: stromboli
directions: Mix mustard and mayonnaise together; set aside. Using a large ungreased cookie sheet, roll dough into a rectangle about 12 x 15-inches. Down the center, layer ham, grated cheese, salami and Provolone. Sprinkle garlic salt and oregano over cheese to taste. Spread sides of bread with mustard mixture. Fold sides of bread over meat and cheese filling; overlap at center. Seal with water. Do the same for the ends of dough. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool, then cut.

title: punch
directions: Makes 2 1/2 gallons punch.
Add 2 bottles ginger ale at serving time.

title: wine jelly
directions: Soak gelatine in cold water.
Add salt and sugar.
Pour boiling water over this.
Then add lemon and orange juice.
When it has cooled, add wine.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: apple crisp
directions: Toss apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Spread in bottom of 11 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: banana split cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine. Pat in bottom of pan.
Bake 10 minutes and then cool.

title: freezer french toast
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg. Place bread on rimmed baking sheet.
Pour mixture over bread and let stand for a few minutes.
Turn slices over and let stand until all mixture is absorbed.
Freeze, uncovered, until firm.
Package airtight if you intend to keep it frozen for more than 1 day.

title: peach cobbler(any other fruits)
directions: Melt butter in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Arrange peaches on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until browned. Yield: 6 servings.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve
gelatine
in
4 tablespoons ice water.
Add 1 cup boiling
water.
Set
aside
to cool.
Combine pineapple, sugar, salt
and lemon juice.
Add to cooled gelatine mixture. Let practically
congeal
and fold in 2 boxes Dream Whip (prepare as 1 box).
Rub
brown off the cake and break into bite-size pieces.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Put peanut butter and jelly all over the bread.
Then go wash your hands and face.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, except blueberries. Mix for about 5 minutes. Wash blueberries and drain, then coat with flour. (Note: Blueberries should be fresh or frozen.) Mix with batter and spoon into muffin pans. Bake at 350° until light brown and done.

title: jiffy porcupine
directions: Mix beef, rice, onion and seasonings.
Form into small balls. Fry in hot Wesson oil, turning frequently until light brown, but not crusty, on all sides.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Mix well. Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Beat eggs with water and set aside.
Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and paprika.
In large skillet, heat oil (about 1/2 inch).
Dip chicken breasts into the egg mixture and then into crumb mixture.
Fry chicken in the hot oil until golden brown on both sides.
Remove chicken to a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken in one layer in pan.
Drizzle tomato sauce over chicken. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese evenly over top.
Sprinkle top with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until piping hot and cheese is melted and lightly browned.
Serves 8.

title: scalloped potatoes dauphinaise
directions: Rub garlic over bottom and sides of large shallow baking dish. Pat potatoes dry with paper towels.
Layer half the potatoes, cheese, butter, salt and pepper in baking dish.
Repeat layers. Pour in milk around sides of dish.
Bring to a boil over low heat. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender. Remove excess liquid with bulb baster.
Bake for 5 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender, liquid is absorbed and top is browned.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican beans(to be cooked in slow cooker)
directions: Put soaked and drained beans into slow cooker.
Add water and all other ingredients.
Cover and cook on low or high; add water, if needed.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots.
Slice or chop pepper and onion. Alternate layers of carrots and onion and pepper.
Blend together well the soup, oil, sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce and salt to taste.
Pour sauce over carrots and refrigerate overnight.

title: party fruit punch
directions: Mix juices and extract.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add to juices.
Add sugar, stirring thoroughly.
Pour over ice and serve.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add broccoli and onion. Cook over medium heat until broccoli is thawed.
Continue cooking, according to package directions or until broccoli is done, 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In one bowl, mix together cooked pumpkin, granulated sugar, eggs and oil.
In a different bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, allspice, baking soda and salt.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake mix according to package directions. Pour half batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and margarine.
Blend well.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over baked cake.
Add remaining batter.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Check for doneness (not gooey).

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box. Bake and let cool.
Make jello. Cut small slits in cake and pour jello in cake.
Put in refrigerator until jello gets firm, then cover with Cool Whip.

title: mexican fiesta food
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add bottle of picante sauce, refried beans, tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water; mix well.
Put a layer of chips in a pan.
Top with meat mixture, then pour Velveeta cheese, then top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until melted.

title: dunbar macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water.
Mash tomatoes; add salt, pepper, sugar and onion and simmer 15 minutes.
Brown ground beef; mix together and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients and boil and boil hard 1 minute.
Add peanut butter.
Then add oats.
Drop on greased wax paper.

title: fake coconut pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: cheese and sausage appetizers
directions: In large
bowl, combine cheese, butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Beat
with
mixer	at low speed.
Stir in cooked sausage. Form
dough into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased pan. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sea bass and green beans(servings:  4. preparation time:  0:45.)
directions: Pat fish dry with paper towel.
Cut fish into 2 x 1/2-inch slices.
Toss fish in 1 teaspoon sesame oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt, ginger root and white pepper in medium bowl.
Then coat fish in 1 teaspoon of cornstarch and toss.
Cover and refrigerate 20 minutes.
Snap green beans into halves.
Cut green onion diagonally into 1-inch pieces.
Mix together 1 tablespoon of cornstarch and cold water.
Mix together sugar and 1/4 teaspoon sesame oil.
Heat wok until very hot.
Add 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil and tilt wok to coat side.
Add fish and stir-fry gently until fish turns white.
Remove fish from wok.

title: lemon pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool.
Add pineapple with juice. Chill until slightly thick.
Blend softened cream cheese with other ingredients.
Stir into jello mixture.
Pour into dish and chill.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: When ready to serve, add 1 cup sour cream.
Serve over noodles.
Children really like.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Mix taco mix and refried beans.
Spread in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer other ingredients in order.
Do not cook.
Eat with tortilla chips or Doritos.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Mix together sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add soda, flour, oatmeal and peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
until light brown.

title: chicken cordon bleu(makes 8 servings)
directions: Pound chicken breasts.
Saute chicken breasts.
Sprinkle chicken with seasoning salt.
Wrap chicken first with cheese. Place chicken in center of puff pastry and fold in each corner to seal completely.
Place on cookie sheet.
Place on baking sheet. Coat each one with egg white.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve with gravy or cheese sauce.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of 9 x 9 or 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown hamburg; drain and add salsa.
Heat.
Then put some hamburg and salsa mixture on top of cream cheese.
Then add shredded cheese.
Keep going until hamburg mixture is gone.
Cream cheese is only on the bottom.

title: summertime burgers
directions: Combine egg, onion powder, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, salt, chili powder and barbecue sauce.
Blend well.
Mix in Wheat Chex crumbs and ground beef.
Shape into 6 patties.
Grill 8 to 12 minutes or to desired doneness.
Turn midway during cooking.
Brush with additional barbecue sauce.
Makes 6 hamburgers.

title: lime salad
directions: Combine jello, mini marshmallows and boiling water.
Chill until partially congealed, then add Cool Whip, crushed pineapple and pecans.
Chill until set.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine bread crumbs, butter and milk; pour into buttered dish and cool. Add sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla. Bake for 1 hour at 325°. Serve with sauce.

title: sausage tortilla quiche
directions: Cook sausage according to package directions; drain and cut in slices.
Place 9 tortillas in the bottom of a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Place remaining tortilla in center of plate.
Combine sausage slices and cheeses; sprinkle over tortillas.
Next, sprinkle tomato and chili peppers over cheeses.
Beat eggs, milk, chili powder and salt; pour over the layered ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until puffed up in center. Allow to set 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Form into ball. Refrigerate. Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: slush
directions: Freeze altogether.
To mix, use 1/2 cup Slush and 1/2 cup 7-Up.

title: old fashion chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Line a pie pan with vanilla wafers.
Stir milk, chocolate chips and marshmallows over medium heat until thick.
Cool. Spoon 1/2 quart vanilla ice cream over wafers.
Cover with 1/2 chocolate mixture; repeat.
Put nuts on top and place in freezer for 3 hours.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat when it forms a ball.
Knead on wax paper.
Add food coloring.
Store in airtight container.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Add shredded cheese and crumbled bacon. Toss all with salad dressing.

title: plaza 3 steak soup
directions: Melt oleo. Stir in flour.
Make a smooth base. Gradually add 2 quarts warm water, stirring constantly. Saute meat in a large skillet. Drain. Add meat to soup.
Parboil onions, carrots and celery for 15 minutes. Drain. Add to soup.
Add all other ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: sangria
directions: Mix all ingredients except garnish.
Chill thoroughly.
To serve, add club soda and ice for lightness.

title: chinese chicken and almond spud topping
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Saute chicken until cooked thoroughly.
Remove and reserve.
Add onion and garlic until transparent.
Add broccoli, broth and vinegar.
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce; stir into skillet.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 1 minute.
Add chicken, almonds and pimiento.

title: refrigerator spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add all other ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Place in airtight covered container and store in refrigerator.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and celery in butter until tender. Mix in all other ingredients and either stuff bird or bake in a covered dish, that has been buttered, for 1 hour.
Uncover last 10 minutes of baking.

title: easy ambrosia
directions: In large bowl, place drained fruit cocktail, add Cool Whip to which green food coloring has been added making it a light green color.
*Add marshmallows.
Stir and place in clear glass serving bowl.
Chill until ready to serve.
Refreshing, not heavy after big meal.

title: souvlaki(marinated skewered lamb)
directions: Quarter and separate onion pieces. Quarter then halve green peppers. Halve tomatoes. Divide lamb into 8 portions. Thread each portion on a skewer alternating lamb cubes with vegetables. Combine remaining ingredients to form a marinade. Place skewers in a pan and cover with marinade. Cover pan and refrigerate overnight. Broil or grill for 20 minutes.

title: quick banana malt
directions: Slice banana.
Puree with remaining ingredients in blender. Makes 1 serving.

title: tuna krispie casserole
directions: Combine cream of celery soup, cream of mushroom soup, tuna and cereal.
Place in a lightly greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly or in a microwave for 10 minutes on high.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook egg noodles uncovered in boiling water 20 minutes, stirring occasionally; drain.
Combine mushroom soup, milk, water and Cheddar cheese in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese melts and sauce is hot.
Stir in cooked noodles, turkey, peas and carrots and pimento.
Spoon mixture into greased 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Sprinkle over the top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a large pan (5-quart) heat oil and margarine.
Brown onions, garlic and ground beef on low heat (approximately 15 minutes).
Add tomatoes, corn, chili powder, salt and cornmeal.
In a small bowl, beat together eggs and milk until well mixed.
Add to mixture and stir well.
Cook 20 minutes.
Put into a casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt the chocolate in the coffee over hot water.
Cool.
Beat the egg yolks in a bowl.
Add the sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites gently, but thoroughly.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into a 2-quart souffle dish.
Chill for 6 hours.

title: peanut-raisin mix
directions: Mix peanuts and raisins together.
Store in airtight container.
Serve as a snack or appetizer.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Grease and flour cake pan.
Blend together sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine cake flour and baking soda.
Alternate milk and flour beginning and ending with flour.	Add vanilla; mix well.	Pour into cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Sterilize canning jars.
Put half the peppers and half the vinegar into blender container.
Cover and process at the liquify setting until peppers are liquified.
Repeat with remaining peppers and vinegar.
Combine liquified peppers-vinegar and sugar in a large saucepan and boil slowly for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add liquid pectin; boil hard for 1 minute.
Skim.
Add a few drops of green food coloring.
Pour jelly immediately into hot canning jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Wipe jar rims and adjust lids.
Process 5 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Makes 5 half-pint jars.

title: mary's marvelous bread
directions: Stir in all ingredients.
Then put in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice and enjoy!

title: rich layer fruit cake
directions: Run nuts, raisins and coconut through food chopper.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk (in which soda has been dissolved), jam, spices, flour and chopped ingredients.
Bake in three well-greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and put together with filling.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Melt butter; add flour and powdered sugar.
Mix just until blended.
Press out on pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (or until bubbly and slightly browned).
Serve with rye bread squares or any variety of crackers you like.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut the broccoli into small pieces. Add the onion. Fry some bacon. Blot grease off and crumble into small pieces. Add the cheese.
In a separate bowl, mix the Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over salad.
Toss and refrigerate for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: microwave countryside potatoes
directions: Cook hash browns in package on Full power for 10 minutes.
Turn halfway.
Stir in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 6 minutes on Full power.
Stir.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 6 minutes on Level 5.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Save broth and cook noodles in broth.
Combine sour cream, soups and chicken, cut into small pieces.
Add to cooked noodles and add salt to taste.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle bread on top.
Melt butter and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together and heat in microwave or oven until bubbly. Serve with crackers.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites,
corn syrup, water, sugar and cream of tartar in top of
double boiler.
Beat for 1 minute at high speed to blend.
Beat until mixture forms peaks when beater is raised, about 7 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Continue to beat until thick enough to
spread.	Put
filling between layers of cake, then cover entire
cake	with
icing.
Decorate	with
orange slices after sprinkling sides and top with coconut.

title: peachtree road race
directions: In a large glass mix all ingredients.
Add enough Sprite to fill the glass.
Serve over ice.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Stir well and pour into pan with melted butter.
Bake in oven at 400° for approximately 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Combine crabmeat, bread crumbs, onion, pepper and celery in a large bowl.
Beat together remaining ingredients until smooth. Mix with crab.
Pack into a shallow baking dish or crab shells. Bake at 350° until hot, about 30 minutes.

title: easter jello salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and whip together.
Cool.
Add drained, crushed pineapple and marshmallows; mix altogether.
Fold in Cool Whip.
May add coconut or nuts, if desired.

title: marble cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
To 1/3 of batter add chocolate, sugar, water and soda.
Cut this mixture into remaining 2/3 batter with a spatula.
Bake at temperature and time indicated on cake mix box.

title: braised pork tenderloin(chinese style)
directions: Combine pork and all ingredients in a glass or ceramic baking dish. Cover. Marinate for 8 hours or overnight, turning several times. Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before baking.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add softened margarine and mix with spoon.
Add the rest and mix.
Line cookie sheet with foil and drop by 1/2 teaspoon.
Leave space; they really spread! Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and lift with hand (peel away when hard).
Melt 12 ounce bag of semi-sweet chocolate.
Spread on shiny side.
Place one another on top of each other.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add beans.
Spread Doritos in baking dish.
On top, spread meat, onions and bean mixture.
Mix Ro-Tel tomatoes and soup together.
Spread over meat mixture.
Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef 'n barley soup
directions: Brown meat in cooking fat in Dutch oven or soup pot.
Pour off drippings.
Add water, onion, bouillon, salt and herbs.
Cover tightly and cook slowly 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir in carrots, green beans and celery and continue cooking, covered, 45 minutes or until meat is tender and vegetables are done.
Remove bay leaf.

title: chicken curry rice
directions: Lightly brown chicken with curry to taste.
Make broth per rice serving.
Add additional curry to taste.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.

title: stuffed zucchini squash
directions: Trim ends of zucchini, do not peel.
Cook whole zucchini in boiling water for 5 minutes or until crisp tender.
Cool slightly. Half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4 inch thick shell. Chop pulp, set aside.
Sprinkle shells lightly with salt.
Arrange in a 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine egg margarine, the 1/4 cup Parmesan, onion, parsley and pepper.
Stir in chopped pulp and bread crumbs.
Spoon filling into shells.
Sprinkle with the 1 Tbsp.
Parmesan.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven about 20 minutes until set and heated through.
Serves 6.

title: prune cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix the first 6 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into two 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch greased Pyrex dishes.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Five minutes before removing from oven, spread tops with icing.

title: chocolate covered coconut mounds
directions: Melt together in top of double boiler.
Dip candy with toothpick.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown meat.
Add salt and pepper and rest of ingredients. Cook slowly for 2 to 3 hours.

title: lazy day cake
directions: Cake:
Put all ingredients together in bowl and mix by hand. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot chinese chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In 12 x 9-inch baking dish, combine chicken, celery, water chestnuts, red onion, soy sauce, mayonnaise, noodles with seasoning and soup. Bake in preheated oven 20 minutes. Turn off oven. Stir salad once. Top with almonds. Return to oven 6 minutes.

title: davy crocket bar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well, adding oatmeal and chocolate chips last.
(I spread the chips on top and press into batter.)
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until done in middle.

title: football season stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large, tightly-covered casserole dish.
Bake 5 hours at 275°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Melt butter; stir in flour and salt to make a thick paste and add milk.
Stir constantly until medium white sauce is made.
Add grated cheese; stir until melted.
Place macaroni in 2-quart casserole; pour sauce over and stir.
Bake in 350° oven half an hour or microwave High 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frankfurters dutch treat
directions: Cook
onion
and
pepper
in
margarine
until
tender. Prepare sauce mix as directed, except use 1/2 cup milk.
Blend in 1/2
cup
salad
dressing and dash of Worcestershire sauce. Combine onion,
pepper
and salad dressing mixture with grated carrot
and cooked noodles;
mix
lightly.
Line
sides
of
a 1 1/2-quart casserole with
split lengthwise frankfurters, cut in half.
Spoon noodle mixture into center of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hellmann's chocolate cake
directions: Add dry ingredients; sift in large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise. Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: jeff's lemon chicken
directions: In a plastic bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time; shake to coat.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in margarine until golden brown.
Add lemon juice and mushrooms.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients and put in a baking dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fat ladies
directions: Preheat oven.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan, put cookies 1/4 inch deep.
Flatten.
Cook for 12 to 14 minutes.
Melt caramels with half and half in microwave.
Put chocolate chips over cookie layer.
Cook until chocolate is melted, about 5 minutes.
Spread caramel mixture over cookies.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: 5-star pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper chops to taste.
Smooth mustard on both sides, roll in flour and lightly brown.
Place in shallow baking pan with soup.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; cook 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; cook for 45 minutes.
Place in freezer bags or into glass jars and seal.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks very stiff.
Fold in other ingredients.
Pour into a graham cracker crust pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Chill; top with whipped topping.
Freeze.

title: caramel candy
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Boil milk and 2 cups sugar over low heat.
Add browned sugar.
Melt margarine and add to mixture.
Cook until mixture forms a soft ball when poured into cold water.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Set aside to cool.
Then beat until smooth and thick.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cut into squares.

title: italian beef(serves 10)
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot with 1 cup water and onions until tender (12 hours on low).
Take roast out of liquid and refrigerate until cool.
Refrigerate liquid to let fat harden. Skim fat off top and slice roast.
Put liquid in saucepan and bring to a boil with the seasonings.
Pour over sliced beef in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt butter and mix cocoa.
Mix eggs and sugar.
Add two mixtures to flour.
Add vanilla and nuts and beat well.
Pour into greased floured 8 x 12-inch or similar size pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°.
Start testing with toothpick after 35 minutes. Takes approximately 40 to 45 minutes.
When done, cover cake with marshmallows.
Ice when cake is thoroughly cooled with butter chocolate icing.

title: au gratin party potatoes
directions: In several large bowls, combine potatoes, milk, cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Transfer to 4 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Yield:
about sixty 3/4-cup servings.

title: brown rice and chili chicken
directions: In a large skillet cook chicken in oil 2 minutes or until brown.
Remove and set aside.
Add onion to skillet with green pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add undrained tomatoes, broth, rice and hot sauce.
Bring to boiling.
Remove from heat and spoon into baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top.
Bake covered in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand uncovered until cheese melts. Sprinkle with olives.
May be topped with plain yogurt.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies(yields 4 dozen cookies)
directions: Blend together sugar, oil, cocoa, eggs and vanilla until mixed well.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt into cocoa mixture. Cover and refrigerate until dough is firm enough to handle (at least 6 hours).
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes until tops are crackled.
Remove to cooling rack to cool completely.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir together pineapple and pudding mix.
Then add next three ingredients.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts.
Refrigerate and enjoy. Lo-cal and low-fat.

title: carrot ring
directions: Mix eggs with carrots.
Stand the butter mold with the mixture in a pan of boiling water.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40 minutes.
Turn out onto a hot plate and fill with hot butter peas. Pour melted cheese over ring when ready to serve.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Add margarine and soups. Mix well. Add all other ingredients. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: conch stew
directions: Clean and dice	conchs.
Put
conchs, strips, onion and seasoning in pressure
cooker.
Pour water over meat, cook for 35 minutes.
Check
for
tenderness of meat, if not ready cook 15 minutes more.
Cook 1 hour on gas or electric range.
Makes about 6 servings.
Serve over rice.
Delicious.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix the ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased 8-inch pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except for steak in a large glass bowl and mix well.
Place steak inside and turn several times, coating the steak completely.
Let marinate in covered container for 4 to 5 hours or overnight if possible.
Cook steak so that it is browned on the outside but rare in the center.
Cut diagonally across the grain into thin slices and serve.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers;
pack in
jars.
To each quart jar, add garlic, hot pepper and head
of
dill (1 each per jar).
Bring to a boil 2 quarts
water, salt and vinegar;
pour over cucumbers in jars and seal.

title: pears helene
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Beat in milk and salt.
Blend in peppermint.
Serve hot or cold.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream first three ingredients.
Add eggs; beat well.
Blend in chocolate.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in blender. Add the salad oil slowly while blending. Beat until thick. Add poppy seed and food coloring. Beat until very thick. Store in refrigerator. Will keep in refrigerator a week or longer.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: potato candy
directions: Combine vanilla and potatoes, slowly add sugar and mix into stiff dough.
Take small portion and roll out thin on waxed paper. Spread with desired amount of peanut butter.
Roll like jelly roll.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut into small bite-size pieces.

title: sweet spicy mustard
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Boil only long enough to blend well.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with 1 cup of sugar and salt in a small saucepan with heavy bottom.
Mash 1 1/2 baskets of the berries and add with the lemon juice to the saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 2 to 3 minutes after mixture comes to a simmer.
Pour into a bowl and place in a pan of ice water to cool.
When cool, fold in remaining 1 1/2 baskets of sliced berries.
Whip cream with sugar until soft peaks form.
Pour cooled filling into cooled crust.
Cover pie with whipped cream.
If desired, put small amount of whipped cream into pastry bag and pipe rosettes around pie edges.
Sliced strawberries can be arranged as a flower in middle of pie as a garnish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Mix together and bake 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup butter or margarine, eggs, flour, salt, vanilla, chopped nuts and Hershey's syrup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool cake completely before frosting.

title: chocolate fudge dessert
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Then mix in milk, butter and nuts.
Pour in a greased 13 inch cake pan and spread batter out. Make sauce and pour gently over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: amber marmalade
directions: Cut apricots into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients in a large, heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often. Cook 15 minutes or until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Boil rapidly, stirring often, until syrup is thick.
Ladle at once in hot jars.
Top with a layer of melted paraffin.

title: fruit swirl coffee cake
directions: Beat sugar, butter, shortening, flavoring and eggs.
Beat well for about 3 minutes.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Spread half of batter in a large cake pan.
Spread pie filling on batter. Drop remaining batter by spoon over filling.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze while still warm.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Cut chicken up into 1-inch squares.
Place in flat glass baking dish.
Mince garlic and spread over chicken evenly. Sprinkle oregano and parsley evenly over chicken.
Cut butter into 1/2 x 1-inch squares and place evenly on top of chicken.
Pour wine evenly over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place chicken in broiler; stir frequently or chicken will burn.
Cook until white in color and done, approximately 15 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cherry juice.
Chill and partially congeal.
Add cherries and olives.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with banana, beating well after each addition.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: lo-fat bagel chips
directions: Slice partially frozen bagels very thin (being careful not to slice fingers).
Spray cookie sheet with butter spray and spread bagel slices on it.
Spray bagel slices lightly and shake on seasonings, being generous with garlic and Italian seasoning, but light on salt.
Bake in a 400° oven for 4 minutes.
(Your oven may vary in heat.
Check after 3 minutes.)
Yields 2 cups of bagel chips.

title: fudge bars
directions: Combine butter and chocolate in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Cook until chocolate and butter melt.
Combine sugar and eggs in a mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Add chocolate mixture; beat well.
Stir in flour and salt just until blended.
Stir in pecans and vanilla. Pour into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.
Let cool slightly.
Spread with Chocolate Frosting while slightly warm.
Cool.
Cut.
Yield:
4 1/2 dozen.

title: classic potato salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, prepared mustard, celery seed and pepper in small bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Combine potatoes, celery, onions, radishes, green peppers and parsley in large bowl. Add ingredients of small bowl into large bowl.
Toss to mix. Cover.
Refrigerate several hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: martha's supper
directions: Finely chop cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Mix with salt and let stand for 30 minutes.
Squeeze out any liquid.
Heat margarine in deep skillet.
Add vegetables, sugar, milk and pepper.
Cook over low heat 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender to slightly golden.
Stir frequently.
Add noodles, horseradish, cottage cheese, lemon juice and celery seed.
Heat through.
This can also be made by placing into greased casserole and bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes.
If done this way, add about 3/4 cup milk after filling casserole.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Slice apples into pie plate.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
In bowl, mix rest of ingredients until smooth.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves about 6.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except onion rings. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish (greased) at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put French fried onion rings on top and cook about 5 more minutes.
You may put a little grated cheese on top too.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients.
Drain and add other ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut cookie into 1/8-inch thick slices. Line 14 inch pizza pan with cookie slices overlapping slightly. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mix well.
Spread mixture over cookie crust. Arrange fruit over cream cheese layer.
Glaze with combined marmalade and water.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: fruit salad delight
directions: Drain all fruits.
Mix together with the pecan bits, coconut and sour cream.
Chill before serving.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix well together and bake in two crusts.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients in 2 cans tomato juice until tender. Add beef, corn, green beans, peas, tomatoes and another can of tomato juice.
Bring to boil; add salt and pepper.
Then add brown sugar.
This freezes real well!!

title: rare and delicious roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Have meat at room temperature.
Rub seasoning of choice on meat.

title: summer vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Unroll crescent rolls onto pan; pinch perforations in dough to make one large sheet.
Bake according to package directions.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Combine yeast, water and sugar in mixing bowl.
Allow to stand until yeast is dissolved and begins to foam (about 5 minutes). Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and flour.

title: carne asada
directions: Mix carne asada, steak sauce, Season-all and onion.
Let it set for 20 minutes.
Cook on stove or it can be barbecued.

title: old fashioned soda crackers
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda and 1/4 teaspoon of salt. With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Add buttermilk and stir with a fork until well combined.
Knead into a ball.
Preheat oven to 350°.
On a lightly floured board, roll out dough 1/8-inch thick.
With a floured 3-inch round cutter, cut into crackers.
Lightly grease several baking sheets.
Prick tops several times with the tines of a fork.
Sprinkle with some of the remaining salt.
Bake until lightly browned on edges, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool baked crackers completely on wire rack.
Store tightly covered.

title: no bake brownies
directions: In a double boiler over hot water, melt chocolate and butter until smooth. Grease a 12 x 8 baking dish. Combine crumbs and walnuts. Stir in milk and vanilla, then chocolate mix. Pat evenly. Let stand at room temperature 2 hours. Cut and serve. Yield 24 brownies.

title: marinated beef brisket
directions: Line broiler pan with foil.
Wrap brisket in foil with remaining ingredients.
Marinate overnight.
Bake 4 to 5 hours at 225° to 275° in the foil that it was marinated in.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Add flour gradually. Spread dough in greased 9 x 7-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° until medium brown and dough seems set, but not brown on edges, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Place chocolate squares on dough.
They will melt.
After they have melted, spread out chocolate.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cool and cut into bars. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: coconut buttermilk pie
directions: For 2 pies, increase flour to 3 tablespoons, buttermilk to 3/4 cup and pie shell to 2.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Goes well with any beef dish.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Beat 2 minutes. Pour into 2 loaf pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: country cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for the 1/4 cup ham. Shape into a ball, coating with remaining ham.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: wild rice and turkey salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Cool.
Add turkey, mayonnaise, French dressing, salt, almonds and celery.
Chill. Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Add to the chilled turkey mixture just before serving.
Serve on lettuce.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry hamburger and drain grease.
Put rest of ingredients in a large pan with hamburger.
Let simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Chop eggplant; cook down low and stir in egg.
Pour in casserole dish and top with cornbread crumbs, tomatoes and onions. Pour milk over mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir milk and sugar in saucepan over heat. Bring to boil. Boil for 3 minutes. Add marshmallows. Add peanut butter. Mix well with spoon. Pour into greased pan. Refrigerate. Cut into squares.

title: hemphill's rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine with onion 1 minute in microwave oven.
Combine remaining ingredients with margarine and onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, then for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: three-bean salad
directions: In large bowl, toss beans and onions.
Combine oil, vinegar, garlic powder and sugar.
Shake well until blended.
Pour over beans.
Seal; cover bowl.
Refrigerate minimum of 3 hours.

title: zesty squash(microwave)
directions: Place margarine and onion in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High until margarine melts.
Add remaining ingredients except tomato.
Toss to coat.
Cover.
Microwave at High until squash is tender, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time. Stir in tomato.
Cover; let stand 2 minutes.

title: sunday night skillet supper
directions: Melt margarine in skillet on low heat.
Add potatoes, onions and green pepper.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour eggs over potatoes.
Arrange sausage over eggs.
Cover and cook until eggs are set, about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese melts.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Serves 6.

title: angel cake delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugars with electric mixer. Pour over broken pieces of cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix well. Spread pie filling evenly over cake.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Place margarine or butter in medium bowl; microwave, uncovered, on High for 30 to 60 seconds until melted.
Add bread crumbs; toss until well coated.
Mix remaining ingredients. Arrange half of the apple mixture in square dish (8 x 8-inch). Top with half of the bread crumb mixture.
Repeat apples and bread.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 14 to 16 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn every 5 minutes, until apples are tender.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients (except candy Kisses) using lowest mixer speed until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls. Roll in extra sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately press a candy Kiss into the center of each cookie.
(Makes about 4 dozen.)

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Stir together. Cover and chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.

title: salad lover's salad
directions: Cut up lettuce, broccoli, cauliflower and onions into large bowl for first layer.
Sprinkle on top of first layer the bacon bits, frozen peas and grated Cheddar cheese for second layer. Cover all with Miracle Whip and sugar on top.
Chill 6 hours at least.
Toss before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Mix brown sugar and Karo syrup.
Boil.
While waiting to boil, spray cooking spray on 13 x 9-inch long pan (do not grease), then measure cereal into pan.
Once sugar and syrup mixture has boiled, take mixture off stove.
Thoroughly combine peanut butter in same pot.
Pour entire mixture over cereal.
When cool slightly, press mixture with hands to help flatten in pan.
Melt chocolate chips. Spread on top and cool.
May need to be refrigerated.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: beet salad
directions: This will make 1 gallon jar full and will keep all winter. Does not have to be canned.
Stir occasionally when taking some out for a meal.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Chop in butter or margarine.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Cook in double boiler until butter melts. Pour in unbaked pie shell, bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until it is firm.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix softened margarine with flour, sugar and pecans.
Pat out in 12-inch pizza pan.
Brown slightly in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger meat.
When done wash and drain.
Add hamburger meat and spaghetti sauce.
Spray cake pan with vegetable spray.
First layer will be the meat sauce, spread evenly over pan.
Next put a layer of noodles then meat sauce, then Mozzarella cheese.
