Continue with meat sauce, noodles and cheese until pan is full.
The last layer will be cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: very good, good for you crackers
directions: Mix dry ingredients well in large bowl.
In small bowl or pint measure, mix water and oil with a whisk or fork to emulsify. Slowly pour liquid mixture into the dry mix and stir, then knead lightly and divide dough into two parts.
Roll out each part with rolling pin to cover a large cookie sheet.
Spray sheets with Pam. Sprinkle lightly with salt (in addition to salt in recipe) and with sesame or caraway seed.
Roll lightly again and then mark squares with a pastry wheel to desired size.
Place one sheet at a time in a preheated 400° oven, then immediately turn oven down to 350° and bake for 25 minutes.
After 25 minutes, turn oven off, but leave crackers in another 5 to 10 minutes.
Watch carefully, as they brown easily.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend together zucchini, oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans; bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: one day cucumber pickles
directions: Wash
and
slice
cucumbers (1/2 inch).
In a container mix water and lime.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours. Remove and
wash
times.
Put
into kettle (stockpot).	Mix salt, sugar,
spices
and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers.	Let stand 3 hours.
Place pot on stove, bring to a boil, simmer 30 minutes. Pack into hot jars and seal.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream the powdered sugar and margarine.
Add egg.
Stir in flavorings.
Add sifted flour with cream of tartar and soda.
Add salt.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Dough can be rolled and cut into shapes or made into balls and pressed with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream sugar and well beaten eggs.
Mix and sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk, then add other ingredients and vanilla.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and garlic.
Drain grease.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, pepper, tomato sauce and paste.
Let mixture simmer for 20 minutes.
Boil lasagne noodles.
Layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan:
noodles, meat mixture, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, until bubbly.
Serve hot!

title: gelatin ice cream dessert
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Pour into individual dessert glasses or serving bowls.
Chill until set, about 30 minutes. Garnish with fruit if desired.

title: berries and cream
directions: Combine berries in a shallow glass serving dish.
Drain excess liquid off Ricotta.
Puree in food processor until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and Amaretto.
Blend well.
Spoon into serving dish. Serve beside berries and dip fruit.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the sugar and milk until it forms a soft ball when a small amount is dropped in a bowl of cold water.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla, marshmallow creme and peanut butter.
Mix well and fast then spread in a buttered pan.
Cut when cool.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Grease two 12-hole muffin pans.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Melt the red hot candies and the sugar in the water.
Bring to boil and add the apples.
Add drops of red food coloring to make bright red.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes or until apples are tender.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add rhubarb and 1 cup sugar.
Cook until rhubarb is tender.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, egg yolks and milk (I used ordinary milk, didn't change it) and salt.
Put in rhubarb and cook until thick.
Cool.
Put in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: cheese lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Mix tomato sauce with cottage cheese, basil, salt, Worcestershire sauce and onions.
Arrange alternate layers of noodles, American cheese and sauce mixture in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs mixed with grated cheese.
Bake in 375° oven about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, mix together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, mixing well. Add pineapple with juice, mashed carrots and coconut.
Stir well. Add in flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, and nuts.
Mix completely. Pour into greased 13 x 18 jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely, then frost.

title: broccoli with ginger
directions: Rinse broccoli in cool water.
Cut florets off; reserve.
Peel tough outer layer from stems; grate stems and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Add garlic, ginger and oil.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add florets; re-cover and microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, or until crisp-tender. Remove garlic and ginger; sprinkle with salt.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Put beef in roaster.
Add next 3 ingredients (in order) in layers over the beef (do not stir).
Cover roaster and bake for 4 1/2 hours at 325°.
Shred meat with a fork.
Serve on rolls for sandwiches.

title: banana split
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 2/3 cup melted margarine and press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine and beat together softened butter or margarine, confectioners sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Spread over graham cracker crumbs.
Drain pineapple.
Slice bananas and soak for few minutes in the pineapple juice to prevent browning.
Drain banana slices and put pineapple and bananas on top of mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top of fruit.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Drizzle chocolate syrup on top and top with halved maraschino cherries.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: In blender, mix thoroughly 1 ounce Blue cheese, buttermilk, garlic and both sauces.
Add mayo and sour cream.
Stir in remaining cheese.

title: venison shoulder roast
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Place the venison in a roasting pan. Add the oil, wine, water, mushrooms and carrots.
Sprinkle the remaining spices and flavorings over the roast.
Top with the bacon slices.
Cover with foil and roast for 1 1/2 hours (to an internal temperature of 140° to 150°) until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add flour gradually and mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
The dough will be very stiff.
Roll in wax paper.
Chill or freeze.
Slice thin.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: aunt nita's chicken casserole
directions: Mix
chicken, soups, bouillon cubes (dissolved), grated onion and
the egg (chopped up); pour into a Pyrex dish.	Mix flour, butter
and milk; pour over ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° until top is brown, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water for 5 minutes.
Heat coffee and chocolate together until chocolate is melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved. Beat egg yolks thoroughly.
Add yolks, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and vanilla to chocolate mixture; mix well.
Chill until slightly thick.

title: jumbo pasta shells
directions: In
large
saucepan, combine spinach in small amount of water. Cover
and simmer 3 to 5 minutes; drain well.
Chop up spinach and
set
aside.
Cook chopped onion in butter or oil until tender, but not brown.
Add spinach and heat thoroughly. Combine egg, 3 cheeses, nutmeg and spinach mixture.
Stuff 20 cooked shells
with
filling.
Pour
spaghetti
sauce in baking dish.
Place filled shells on top.	Pour other half of sauce over shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee cake(18 slices)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Beat egg yolks thoroughly; beat in milk and yeast mixture.
In large bowl or food processor, combine 3 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until particles are fine.
Transfer to bowl if using food processor.
Stir in yeast mixture and lemon peel.
Cover, let rise 30 minutes.
Stir in about 1/4 cup flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead, adding flour only if necessary, to prevent sticking, until dough is smooth and satiny.
Place in greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.

title: pineapple up-side down cake
directions: Pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350°F for 45 min.
Invert when done.

title: tater tot and beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onion; drain off fat. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish one layer of meat and onion. Add soup evenly over meat.
Place a layer of frozen Tater Tots. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with cheese. Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter. Beat eggs, sugar and butter together. Add other ingredients and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake 30 minutes at 275°, then bake at 300° until golden brown. This makes 2 pies.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Mix gelatine and cold water.
Heat sugar, lemon juice, vinegar and V-8 juice to boil.
Mix with gelatine mixture.
Add chopped vegetables to fill mold (8 1/2 inches).
Chill until set.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Prepare pickling syrup.
Add peeled peaches (whole or half) to syrup; simmer until peaches are tender.
Remove spice bag.
Pack peaches in clean hot jars; cover with syrup.
Seal immediately. Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Place rolls in greased 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and butterscotch pudding mix over top of rolls.
Dot with butter and let sit overnight.
Bake according to package directions.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pork and bread.
Marinate pork in mixture for 4 to 6 hours.
Bake pork for 45 minutes in 350° oven, turning once.
Slice pork into 1-inch slices and serve on sliced and buttered baguettes.

title: not so spooky spiders
directions: Stir chocolate, Krispies and coconut together.
Drop spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Quickly stick "legs" into sides; add eyes. Refrigerate until set, about 15 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain well.
Add other ingredients and cover.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: wonder rice
directions: Use 1 3/4 or 2-quart casserole dish.
Dump all ingredients in. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until mushrooms come to top and absorb liquids.
Stir if you want before serving.

title: crab deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs and prepare for deviling.
Add other ingredients and stuff.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine together.
Mix in sugar and cocoa. Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix and pour into greased pans.
Chill, cut in squares.

title: philly 3-step cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix.
Pour into 1 prepared graham cracker crust (6 ounce or 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Spread with a 21 ounce can of cherry pie filling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Pork chops should be 1-inch thick.
Have a pocket cut in chop for stuffing.
Soak dried bread in water, then squeeze dry.
Mix well with apples, onions, celery and seasonings to make stuffing. Divide stuffing equally and stuff in each chop.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place rice over the bottom of a large baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts over rice.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not uncover dish until ready to serve.

title: toffee
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan and cook over medium heat until it boils.
Time for 10 minutes while stirring constantly. Pour immediately on buttered cookie sheet that has chopped nuts spread on it.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over candy and wait until it softens a little, then spread with butter knife.
(I put my chips through a nut chopper so they melt faster.)
Set in refrigerator for at least 1/2 hour, then break into pieces.

title: walnut cake(dios torta)
directions: Butter 2 large 9-inch layer cake pans; place a circle of waxed paper or brown paper in the bottom and butter that as well.
Set the pan aside.
Preheat the oven to 375°.
Beat the egg whites with a pinch of salt until foamy; continue beating until very stiff. Set aside.
With an electric mixer, beat the egg yolks with sugar until light yellow and very creamy.
Blend the walnuts and bread crumbs together; fold them into the egg yolk mixture.
Mix a heaping tablespoonful of the beaten egg whites into the batter to lighten it.
Lightly fold in the remainder of the whites.
The batter should be evenly mixed but not overworked.
Pour into the cake pans; bake for 20 minutes or until the cake springs back when touched.
Remove from oven; cool for 10 minutes in the pans. Invert onto a cake rack; quickly remove all the paper from the bottoms of the layers.
Cool completely before filling and frosting cake.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut squash/zucchini into bite-sized pieces. Cook in boiling water for 3 minutes. Drain. Put squash/zucchini into a 9x13 baking dish. In separate bowl, mix together butter and stuffing. Add remaining ingredients. Spread this mixture on top of squash/zucchini. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix all.
Take out chops and mound stuffing on top of each chop.
Return to oven to finish cooking.
At start, why not put potatoes in to bake.
This is a great meal.
Enjoy.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together apples and 1 cup of sugar; set aside.
Add the other cup of sugar and all dry ingredients in a separate bowl; mix well.
Add eggs, vanilla and vegetable oil together.
Mix liquids into dry mixture.
Fold in apples and sugar.
Place in Bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground chuck with meat tenderizer, garlic salt and pepper. Combine in soup kettle with remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours, skimming off any grease or foam that rises to top.
Serve with toasted white bread cut into 4 strips.
May substitute or add any vegetables desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Bread is done when you insert a toothpick in top and it comes out dry.

title: meal in one
directions: In a skillet brown the meat and onions until tender and meat is done.
Stir to separate meat and pour off grease.
Add the soups,
water,
pepper,
beans and carrots, pour into two-quart shallow
baking dish.
Spoon mashed potatoes across top of casserole,
then
sprinkle
some
shredded cheese over the mashed potatoes.
Bake
at
350° for 30 minutes, until hot and cheese is melted.

title: mike's teriyaki
directions: Mix ingredients.
Marinate beef strips or chicken for several hours or overnight.

title: corn pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: To serve, garnish each with lemon leaves, strawberry halves, blueberries and nectarine wedges.

title: cocoa mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl; add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely. Frost.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook potatoes, cut in small chunks, until soft and add extra water
to potatoes when cooking.
When soft, just add couple of tablespoons of rice and potatoes together and add a can of tomato soup and milk.
Don't let boil.
Serve with sandwiches or fruit.

title: mexican mound taco meal
directions: Follow instructions on taco seasoning mix for browning meat. I serve this meal, in my kitchen, a big pot of meat simmering on the stove.
A wooden salad bowl of Doritos and seven bowls of the remaining ingredients on the table.
Each one's plate starts with a mound of Doritos, then a spoon of piping hot meat, then lettuce, tomatoes, etc. etc.
This is the Bush family's favorite.

title: dream bars
directions: Sift and measure flour; add butter and sugar and mix to a crumbly mixture, using the fingertips or a pastry blender.
Pat mixture into jelly roll pan and bake in moderate oven at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread Part 2 over crust.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix above ingredients together, stirring dry pudding in well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Best if made night before using.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix until well blended.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cube chicken and add enough Hellmann's mayonnaise to mix.

title: banana date-nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl and let stand about 5 minutes to absorb moisture.
Drop cookies by large spoonfuls onto lightly oiled baking sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Slice meat thin
and
brown in oil rapidly.
Add sliced onions, scallions, mushrooms, spinach and bamboo shoots.
Cook 5 minutes, stir.
Add
soy
sauce,
beef broth and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook uncovered for 15 minutes.
Stir a few times.

title: onion mushroom turkey gravy
directions: Combine giblets (except liver) and neck with bay leaf and water in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling; stir in soup. Simmer 40 minutes. Add liver and simmer 20 minutes until tender. Remove giblets. Measure broth and add water (if necessary) to make 3 1/2 cups.

title: baked noodles and ham
directions: Put a layer of noodles in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with ham and cheese, then cover with a layer of white sauce. Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle top with cheese. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: onion-tomato frittata
directions: Saute onions in 3 tablespoons oil in 10-inch skillet with heat resistant handle, until tender.
Saute green pepper 1 minute.
Beat eggs, 1/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add to skillet; cook over medium-low heat, lifting bottom with spatula as eggs set, about 3 minutes.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until top is almost set.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix the ingredients together and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: onion soup casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until hot.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In a well-buttered, 2-quart casserole, place layers of vegetables in order given.
Season each layer with salt and pepper as you go along.
Lay potatoes flat in the bottom of the greased casserole.
In the meantime, brown ground beef in a skillet.
On top of the potatoes, slice carrots.
Pour peas over carrots.
Slice onions and layer over the peas, then slice celery over the onions. Put the browned, drained ground beef over the celery.
Mix the liquid from the peas with can of tomato soup and pour over all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter, dipped in baking mix.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place, about 30 minutes or until soft and puffy.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ferden
directions: Melt magarine in heavy saucepan.
Add the smaller amount of flour and salt.
Add milk; cook until like custard.
Cool enough to be able to add egg yolks without cooking them; beat in one at a time.
Add raisins (soaked in water and drained), 1/4 cup sugar and cardamom.
Add yeast, dissolved in warm water, and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add flour.
Beat egg whites with a pinch of salt until stiff; fold into mixture.
Let rise about 3 1/2 hours or to the top of the bowl.
Drop into deep fat (375°) by teaspoonfuls; cook until brown.
Drain on paper toweling.
Roll in granulated sugar while still warm.
Best eaten when just fried and still warm.

title: dad's quick sauce
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
In a skillet brown meat and drain.
Cook fettucini according to package.

title: chili
directions: Wash beans and cook until almost soft.
Brown hamburger and cook onions until transparent.
Add hamburger, onions and other ingredients to beans.
Finish cooking until beans are soft.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: holiday cheese ring
directions: Grate cheeses, onion, and garlic together.
Mix well with a food processor or electric mixer.
Add mayonnaise and hot sauce. Mix until well blended.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, heat the first 4 ingredients until boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, until rice is tender, stirring occasionally (45 minutes to 1 hour).
In small bowl, beat the eggs slightly; stir in small amount of hot rice mixture. Slowly pour egg mixture back into rice mixture, stirring rapidly to prevent lumping.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 5 minutes (do not boil).
Remove from heat.
Stir in the vanilla extract.
Cool in refrigerator until chilled, about 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: dirty rice
directions: Heat the chicken stock in a 12-quart pot and add the gizzards and livers along with the salt, Worcestershire sauce and cayenne. Cover and lightly boil for 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes and cook until tender.
Boil eggs, shell and grate. Add potatoes, grated eggs and salt.

title: zoe's favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies may not seem done, but check bottom, they will firm.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine
cornstarch, sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind. Beat egg
yolks	and add to cornstarch mixture.	Gradually add boiling water.
Heat to boiling over direct heat and then boil gently
4 minutes,
stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell.	Beat egg
whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat in 6 tablespoons sugar.	Spread meringue over top of pie. Bake 4 to 5 minutes in 425° oven until browned.

title: homemade hot dog chili
directions: Boil onion and hamburger in water.
Add vinegar.
Cook until done.
Drain well.
Add salt and pepper, chili powder and sugar. Stir well.
Add ketchup and mustard stirring again.
Simmer on low until ready to serve on hot dogs.

title: chicken - dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken and de-bone.
Cut chicken into small cubes. Layer in pan.
Place cream of chicken soup over the chicken. Place stuffing mix over the soup.
In a saucepan; melt 1 stick of butter into the chicken broth. Pour broth over stuffing mix until entire mixture is moist.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked fruit turnovers
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°. Cut each pie crust into 6 wedges. Combine fruit filling and pecans. Spoon evenly in center of 6 wedges. Top with remaining wedges. Moisten edges of pastry with water, pressing to seal, and crimp edges with a fork. Place turnovers on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: doris' lemon dessert
directions: Beat the 6 egg yolks until light; add grated lemon rind, lemon juice and sugar.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Soak gelatine in cold water.
Add to custard and let cool.
In a large bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add the sugar.
Fold custard in.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Add flour mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Spoon on a greased sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in baking pan.
Mix water and lemon juice and pour over peaches.
Mix sugar, flour, oats and cinnamon.
Add margarine to dry mixture and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Yields 4 servings. Contains 220 calories per serving.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll in balls and press down.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: holiday baked ham
directions: Wash ham and dry.
Cut off rind and half of fat.
Wrap ham in foil.
Line shallow roasting pan with foil.
Place ham in pan; place in a preheated 350° oven and bake for 3 hours.
Remove from oven, turn back foil and pour off drippings.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: dan's "dry creek" chicken and vegetable soup
directions: In large stockpot, add chicken stock or water.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken breast and poach for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from liquid and set aside to cool.
Reduce heat to simmer and add all other ingredients and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Shred cooled chicken and add back to soup at end of the 35 to 40 minutes, then simmer for additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Season to taste when all ingredients are added and at end, check taste and add additional seasoning if needed to suit taste.

title: peanut butter cookie mix
directions: In a large bowl, cream together peanut butter, margarine and sugars.
Blend in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add, mixing well.
Keep dough in covered container in refrigerator.

title: plain pie crust
directions: Yields 3 (10-inch) double crusts or 1 large cobbler.
Sift flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry.
Blend until mixture looks like meal.
Sprinkle water, a little at a time. Press together until you form a ball.
Let stand several minutes. Roll out.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until smooth. Add flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into egg mixture. Add nuts, apples and vanilla. Bake in greased pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in bananas and egg.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in mini morsels. Spread in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes about 6 dozen bars.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 325°, stirring a few times to combine flavors.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in flavorings.
Bake at 325° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Cook 15 minutes and shake to loosen before turning over.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve plain or with a couple tablespoons warm peach or strawberry preserves.
Makes 12 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Into blender combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Slowly add vegetables and process until they are slightly chunky.
Stir in salad dressing mix by hand.
Chill and serve.

title: orange julius(similar)
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Start at medium speed to crush ice then high speed to make foamy.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Place apples in 2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Mix 2/3 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour together, and sprinkle over apples. Sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Dot with butter.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add shortening, milk and egg.
Blend thoroughly with a fork.
Drop over fruit with a spoon.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Delicious warm with cream or ice cream.

title: creamy peanut popsicles
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, then milk.
Pour mixture into popsicle molds and freeze for 3 hours.
Hold molds under warm water for a few seconds to loosen popsicles.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix meat and vegetables.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Dissolve tapioca in cocktail and pour over meat and vegetable mixture.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not peek!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: parmesan potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in water for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Drain well and return to pot.
Add butter and mash well. Add milk, eggs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper; mash until smooth.
Spoon into a lightly greased shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes, until puffed and golden.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Mix all ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Put in casserole dish.
Crush crackers and spread on top.
Cut margarine in small pieces and spread over crackers. Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix these together and shape into 13X9 pan or 2 8X8 pans.
Beat 2 pkg.
Dream Whip according to directions.
After it peaks add 2 cups sugar.
Then beat in an 8 oz. pkg. of cream cheese (room temp.)
Pour into pan.
Spread 1 can blueberry pie filling over top.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: italian tuna fish salad
directions: In salad bowl, add cucumber, tomato, scallions, salt, pepper and oregano; mix well.
Add tuna; mix again.
If needed, add a bit more olive oil.

title: dandelion wine
directions: Stir ingredients together and let set 24 hours.
Strain and add 2 yeast cakes and 2 handfuls of raisins.
Let set 40 days covered with cheesecloth.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Combine
sour
and
rice; spread in a large baking pan. Place chicken
pieces
on
top
and sprinkle chicken with any desired seasonings
(seasoned
salt,
pepper,
garlic powder, whatever). Cover
with
foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and cook another 30 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: carrot pudding(a steamed pudding)
directions: Grind the carrots and potatoes and place in mixer bowl. Sprinkle soda over carrots and potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Place mixture into 5 chunky soup (Campbell's) cans about 2/3 full.
Place a double square of aluminum foil over the top of the can and twist edges to hold or place an elastic band over the foil to secure.

Place in a large tall kettle on a rack. Pour hot water into the pan so that it comes up to about 3/4 of the cans. Bring water to a boil and then simmer about 1 hour. Test if done when toothpick inserted in middle of can comes out clean. Time may vary with size of kettle.
I use an 8-quart Revere Ware soup kettle. Be sure the cans cannot tip over.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put the chopped cranberries, walnuts and 1/2 cup of sugar in a buttered 10-inch pie plate or spring-form pan.
Mix the eggs, melted and cooled butter, 1 cup of sugar, flour, salt and almond extract.
Stir the batter until it is smooth and pour it over cranberry walnut mixture.
Bake the cake in the middle of the oven for 40 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Cut together flour and margarine; add 3/4 cup of pecans (save 1/4 cup for topping).
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Mix together powdered sugar and cream cheese; spread over cool cake.
Combine instant pudding and milk; spread over 2nd layer.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecan chips you have kept.
Refrigerate.

title: 6-week muffins
directions: Add soda to boiling water; cool.
Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs alternately with flour and soda mixture; mix well. Add rest of ingredients.
Makes a huge amount.
Will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Do not stir.
Dip out into greased muffin tins.
Bake for about 25 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: nut horns
directions: Mix cream, butter and sugar.
Add beaten yolks.
Add flour and nuts.
Form into small horns.
Bake at 400° until golden.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix oil and eggs.
Add zucchini and sugar.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes or loaf pan for 45 minutes; grease and flour pans before pouring in batter.
Let cake cool completely before taking out of pan.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Chop the chocolate.
Heat cream in a saucepan stirring until it bubbles.
Remove from heat, add chocolate and stir until melted.
Crush ladyfingers to fine crumbs.
Sift confectioner sugar and cocoa powder into a large bowl.
Mix in the crumbs, almonds and chopped walnuts.
Add bourbon, chocolate cream and butter and mix well.

title: school rolls
directions: Mix together yeast and 1 cup water; let rise.
Mix together sugar, flour and dry milk.
Mix together butter and other cup of water.
Mix all together, adding yeast mixture and butter mixture alternately to dry mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Must use mixer with dough hooks.
Knead on low, then on high until well mixed and smooth.
Let rise in warm place until double.
Knead and shape into rolls by hand or roll and cut out.
Place on 13 x 9-inch pans; brush top with melted butter.
Bake at 375° until brown. Brush again with butter.
For cinnamon rolls, add 1/4 cup sugar to dry ingredients.

title: lefse
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together when warm.
Cool and add flour.
Make into round balls and roll thin on floured board.
Bake on ungreased griddle at 400°.
When done on one side, flip and cook on remaining side.
Yield:
Protein 2 g, fat 3 g, calories 79. One serving = 1/2 bread starch exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: orange-grapefruit nog
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender container. Cover and blend until smooth. Chill or serve over ice. Makes about 4 cups.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oleo.
Add flour and stewed tomatoes.
Add chicken broth and spaghetti which has been cooked and drained.
Add chicken.
Pour into casserole and place 1 large jar mushrooms on top.
Sprinkle the cubed Velveeta on top and stir under the spaghetti mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: You will also need cupcake bake cups.

title: seasoned crumb chicken(microwave)
directions: Melt margarine in 12 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Set aside. Combine rest of ingredients except chicken in flat dish.
Roll chicken in melted margarine, then in seasoned crumbs.
Place chicken pieces in Pam-sprayed baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs on top.
Microwave 20 to 25 minutes on High or until meat is cooked.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Don't overcook.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies #2
directions: Blend
shortening,
sugars
and eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add salt, baking soda and vanilla extract, mixing well. Gradually
add
and
mix
in
the
flour.
Stir
in the chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: pull-apart cinnamon rolls
directions: Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, cinnamon and sugar. Sprinkle pecans on top of brown sugar mixture.
Cut dough into bite size pieces and place over pecans.
Mix butter, milk and pudding together.
Drizzle over dough.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream first 3 ingredients.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Beat in flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Stir in oats, chips, nuts and coconut, if desired.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: turkey fajitas
directions: Prepare Green Pea Guacamole and chill.
Rinse turkey and pat dry.

title: sausage-broccoli quiche
directions: Saute onions and remove.
Cook sausage and crumble.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Bake pie shell 5 minutes at 450° and sprinkle bottom of pie shell after removing from oven with 2 1/2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese.
Layer broccoli, onions, Swiss cheese and sausage in pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over this.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° and then 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples and spices. Spread into a large greased pie plate. Beat next 5 ingredients until smooth.
Pour over apples.

title: rainbow finger jello
directions: Each layer equals 1 box of Jell-O, 1 package Knox gelatine and 1 cup boiling water.
Milk mixture is one can of Eagle Brand milk, 4 packages Knox gelatine and 2 cups boiling water.

title: hamburger barbecue sloppy joes
directions: Brown the beef in a large skillet over high heat. Drain off the excess fat. Reduce heat to medium-high. Add the onions, green peppers, salt and pepper. Saute until the onions and peppers are softened, about 5 minutes. Add the tomato paste. Worcestershire sauce, mustard, vinegar, and brown sugar. Stir to combine. Add water until the sauce is the desired thickness. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer about 10 minutes so the flavors combine. Taste and adjust as needed. Serve on buns, garnished with relish, and or mustard if desired.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: First, beat eggs, sugar and oil, then sift into it the next 5 ingredients.
Blend in pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad - louisiana style
directions: Mix all and heat in microwave or oven just until warm all through.
Serve plain or in a patty shell.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking pan.
Pour salsa over the top.
Bake at 375 degrees and when it is almost done sprinkle cheese over the top and finish baking.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Put some macaroni in a pan with about 8 cups of water.
Then you dump the water out.
If it's Ramen, you can put cheese on it and warm it up for 8 minutes.

title: cabbage with corn flake topping(serves 8 people)
directions: Mix and heat the first 5 ingredients.
Take corn flakes and melted margarine; toss.
Put half into large casserole, alternating cabbage and sauce.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Add remaining corn flake mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: annie's fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, water, salt and sugar and boil until clear. Remove from heat and add dry jello and food coloring.
Put strawberries in a baked pie shell and add the filling to cover the berries.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: snow pudding
directions: Dissolve corn starch in a little cold water.
Add salt and 1/4 cup sugar.
Pur over in boiling water, stirring constantly.
Stir in 2 egg whites, beaten stiff.
Boil 1 minute more.
Set in cool place to cool.
Make a custard of the milk, beaten egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar.
Boil and flavor with lemon.
Serve the custard on the snow.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise, sugar and chives.
Spread on ham slices.
Roll up and fasten with toothpicks.
Chill until firm, then slice.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Place ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Delicious on hot summer days!
Makes 2 servings.

title: macadamia nut bread
directions: Grease 3 mini loaf pans or 1 large loaf pan and line with paper.
In a large bowl, mix pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Sift flour and baking powder over nut mixture.
Put sugar over mixture and mix gently until coated.
Beat 3 eggs in a small bowl until foamy.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over nut mixture and stir until well mixed.
Spoon in desired pans.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes in a 300° oven.
Remove from oven and turn out on wire racks.
Let cool and wrap in foil.
Keep 4 days in refrigerator before serving.

title: cheese salad
directions: Put all together.
Let boil until thick; cool.
Add 1 cup whipped cream and pineapple.
Add 1 cup grated cheese.

title: apple bread
directions: In bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder, and salt. In large bowl, combine eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and apples. Stir in flour mixture. Mix in nuts. Batter will be very thick. Divide into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs, beating until fluffy.
Make paste of cocoa and vinegar; add oleo, flour, salt and soda to mixture.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and food coloring.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: morgan's grandmama's holiday glazed orange rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Place in mixing bowl and cool until lukewarm.
Add 3 tablespoons of margarine, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and yeast.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Add eggs and 1 cup flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour.
Knead.
Place in greased bowl and let rise for 2 hours.
Divide dough in half.
Roll in rectangle.

title: one-loaf
directions: Mix and let stand 10 to 15 minutes the warm water, honey and dry yeast.
Then add and squeeze between fingers, hand over hand, until all is mixed and dough begins to turn loose from fingers.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix milk, pie filling, pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
